title: peanut butter and pork stir-fry
directions: In wok or large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir-fry pork 3 minutes or until pink is gone.
Remove from pan.
Add rest of oil, carrots, pepper, celery and onion; stir-fry for 3 minutes. Add beans; stir-fry for 1 minute or until veggies are tender-crisp.

title: pinwheels
directions: Combine all ingredients except tortillas. Spread mixture on tortillas. Roll up. Slice into pinwheels 1/2-inch thick. Serve along with picante sauce or salsa for dipping.

title: corned beef stew
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots; save the water.
Combine all ingredients in a 3 or 4-quart boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Boil and allow to simmer for 20 minutes.
If needed, add water from potatoes and carrots to make stew thinner. You can add more or less of the Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, salt and pepper to suit your taste.
You may blend and strain tomatoes to remove pulp and seeds.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Wash potatoes and cut them into medium-size cubes. You can peel them if you like, but they are great with the skins on. Spray a 9 x 13 casserole dish with nonstick spray. Place potatoes in the dish and bake for an hour or until tender.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix in large bowl in order given.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Serve cold.

title: herbed chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces and place in casserole dish. Mix soups with 1 cup broth and pour over chicken.
Mix butter and 1 cup broth and stir in stuffing mix.
Spoon this over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: lemony chicken barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir together all ingredients.
Heat to boiling and simmer, stirring occasionally.

title: nancy's holy guacamole
directions: Mash avocado in a bowl. (I have found that a pastry cutter does a great job.) Add remaining ingredients. Chill. Serve with chips or with fresh tomato slices.

title: lucille's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well; add sour cream, Pet milk and pudding mix. Mix on slow for about 2 minutes. Fold in cream that has been whipped. Add vanilla. Pour into freezer container and finish filling with milk. When making strawberry or peach, use about 1 quart of sweetened fruit that has been chopped in blender. When making peach ice cream, use a half teaspoon almond extract. If you make vanilla, use the French vanilla instant pudding.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream together sugar and cream cheese.
Add pineapple, strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Mix.
Fold in Cool Whip and freeze.

title: stuffed artichokes(serves 6)
directions: Cut tips from fresh artichokes and brush with lemon juice. Cook until tender in boiling water to which salt and olive oil has been added. Remove; drain. Remove center of artichokes. Saute mushrooms, garlic and onion in butter until browned. Stir in parsley, cheese and bread crumbs; mix well. Spoon into artichokes and heat at 325° about 15 minutes. Serve hot with melted butter on the side.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Grate zucchini; stir in rest of ingredients.
Oil skillet or griddle and heat to usual pancake temperature.

title: orange whip
directions: Mix together all but Jell-O.
Add dry Jell-O and mix slowly but very thoroughly.
Put in sealed container and chill.

title: aunt nettie's sugar cookies
directions: Mix and roll out quite thin.
Cut with large cookie cutter. Bake at 350°.
Sprinkle with sugar immediately when removing from oven.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O with water. Fold in strawberries and juice. Drain pineapple and add the pineapple, bananas and nuts to Jell-O. Pour half of mixture into a 2-quart oblong pan.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour or until firm.
Spread sour cream on and put remaining mixture on top. Return to refrigerator.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix oil and sugar in separate container.
Add half flour mixture.
Mix well and beat in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Stir in vanilla and remaining flour mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg, until well blended.
Bake in greased 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan until brown (toothpick will be clean when tested).

title: dressing for salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put on your favorite salad.

title: red snapper steaks
directions: Thaw frozen steaks.
Cut into serving size portions and place in well-greased, hinged wire grill.
Combine remaining ingredients except paprika.
Baste fish with sauce and sprinkle with paprika. Cook about 4 inches from moderately hot coals for 8 minutes.
Baste with sauce and sprinkle with paprika.
Turn and cook for 7 to 10 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Serves 6.

title: delicious enchiladas
directions: Brown burger in large skillet.
Place burger in large pan with beans; save grease from meat.
Add flour to medium hot grease; stir to keep from clumping.
Cook to golden brown; add chili mix and tomato sauce, stirring constantly.
Roll burger and bean mixture into tortillas.
Pour sauce over enchiladas, enough to cover completely.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted.
Delicious topped with lettuce, onion, black olives, tomato and picante sauce.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to a mixing bowl with mixed liquid ingredients.
Beat just until smooth.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Cream.
Scald milk and pour into mixture.
Stir to dissolve.
Add egg and let cool.
Mix salt and yeast in one cup of flour and add to cooled mixture.
Then add 3 cups of flour.
Set one hour, covered.
Beat.
Add additional flour (about 1 cup) to make smooth dough.
Let rise double in bulk.
Put in greased pans (muffin tins, two balls of dough).
Let rise again and bake in moderate oven at 350° until brown.

title: rice cream pie
directions: Stir corn syrup and peanut
butter
until
well mixed in a large bowl.
Add Rice Krispies; mix
until well coated.
Press mixture evenly and firmly into a buttered
9-inch
pie pan.
Chill until firm.
Spread ice cream evenly into pie shell.
Cut
into wedges to serve.
Top with fresh fruit: peaches, strawberries.
I like to thicken my fresh fruit a little.
Refreshing after a hot summer day!

title: nacho salad or the 15 minute meal
directions: Heat chili with beans.
Tear lettuce and place in bowl with carrots.
Add diced tomatoes.
Then, add most of the cheese.
Pour on chili with beans.
Remaining cheese is sprinkled on top.
Sour cream can be added.
Nachos can be placed around the bowl or mixed in with the ingredients.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to
Cream butter, margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in
sour
cream.
Pour
half mixture in greased and floured tube
pan.
Top with half mixture of nuts, cinnamon, brown sugar
and sugar.
Repeat these layers.
Swirl the batter with knife.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, milk, lemon juice and then fold in the other ingredients.
Pour into 2 baked crust or 2 graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate one hour or more.
This is delicious and easy to make.

title: bread machine dinner rolls
directions: In bread machine pan, place the first 9 ingredients in order suggested by manufacturer.
Select dough setting (check dough after 5 minutes mixing; add 1 teaspoon flour or water as needed). When cycle is completed turn dough onto lightly floured surface and punch down.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each portion into 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: oven-fried sesame chicken
directions: Place soy sauce in a shallow dish; add chicken, turning to coat.
Remove chicken from soy sauce; discard soy sauce.
Combine sesame seeds and next 3 ingredients in a large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Add chicken; seal bag and shake to coat chicken with sesame seed mixture.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Drizzle margarine over chicken. Bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes or until done.

title: val's favorite salad
directions: Clean all vegetables.
Mix together sour cream and ranch dressing.
Pour over cut up vegetables and let set in the fridge overnight.
Eat 'em up! Yummy, yummy!!

title: oven fried chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In first bowl, combine flour, pepper and paprika.
In second bowl, beat egg whites and milk.
In third bowl, mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Remove skin and fat from chicken, if using pieces that have skin.
Coat chicken with contents of 3 bowls in order.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Put in baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
In ovenproof skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Remove chops from pan and pour off drippings. Blend in soup, milk and thyme.
Stir in green beans.
Arrange chops on top and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Remove cover and cook to desired consistency, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix at low speed 1 minute, then at medium speed for 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a greased Bundt pan.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and glaze.

title: shrimp or crabmeat fettuccine
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo.
Add shrimp or crabmeat.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add jalapeno cheese until melted.
Add half and half. Combine with cooked noodles in casserole dish.
Top with grated American cheese.
Bake until cheese melts at 350°.

title: charcoal grilled pork loin (tenderloin)
directions: Pat pork loins dry.
Combine mustard and marmalade, jam or jelly.
Coat loins with mustard-marmalade mixture.
Tie with string if pork is in 2 sections.
Put on grill and cook until done.
Salt and pepper while cooking.
Slice into 1/2-inch slices.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook 1/2 cup syrup, salt and water until it spins a thread. Beat egg whites until they are stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites, all this at the same time.
After beating this until it begins to thicken or about ready to dip out, add your nuts and vanilla.
Use the size spoon to dip according to size of pieces of candy you want.

title: parmesan sausage wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 long triangles. Place 1 sausage on shortest side of each triangle.
Roll up, starting with shortest side.
Dip in milk; place on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 14 minutes until golden brown.
Remove immediately and serve warm.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: mike's chicken chili
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and pull off bone.
Add onions, peppers, water and crushed tomatoes.
Bring to simmer for about 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour (best next day).

title: mom riley's cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add 1/2 cup milk; mix until smooth.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Add remainder of milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown in 425° oven for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: provolone sandwich
directions: Slice loaves in half lengthwise.
Brush cut sides of bread with olive oil (about 4 teaspoons).
Combine remaining oil and vinegar and set aside.
Arrange 1/4 of tomato on each bottom half. Brush with vinegar mixture.
Arrange 1/4 of cucumber, cheese and onion over tomato.
Brush with remaining vinegar mix.

title: christmas pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Blend sugar and margarine and mix all other ingredients.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 325° for 1 hour. This will make 3 bought pie shells.

title: fancy hash browns
directions: Mix partially thawed potatoes, soup, cheese, salt and pepper. Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the melted butter evenly over the top.
Sprinkle with the cereal.

title: curried pork chops
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, curry powder, salt and pepper. Use to coat both sides of pork chops.
In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook pork chops 7 to 8 minutes until tender and golden brown on both sides, turning pork chops once.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix with mixer.
May be left chunky. Refrigerate several hours to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers, chips or Bugles.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out each half of biscuit, wrap each slice around apple piece and lay in large pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Pour over apples.
Melt 1 stick margarine; pour on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Bring broth and oleo to a boil.
Add noodles and simmer 45 minutes.
Add 3 small cans or 1 large can white chicken chunks. Cook 15 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss steak quickie
directions: Dot
the
center
of
a 20-inch sheet of heavy aluminum foil with
teaspoon
butter
or margarine.
Shake half the contents of 1 envelope onion soup mix on the foil (dry).
Over this, place chuck or round steak with remaining soup mix and 1 teaspoon butter.
Add
fresh
mushrooms
around steak.
Bring foil
up over meat and double-fold edges.
Place in a shallow baking pan. Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Add flour and baking soda, mix well.
Stir in bacon, cornflakes and raisins.
Drop by rounded tablespoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 - 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 2 minutes before removing to wire racks. Store in the refrigerator.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers according to package directions and cool completely.
Make pudding according to package directions.
In large bowl, break one layer of cake into 4 or 5 large chunks and layer in bottom of bowl.
Pour 1/2 of the pudding over the cake. Spread 1 carton of Cool Whip over pudding.
Top with 5 broken candy bars.
Repeat each layer and chill overnight.
Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: olive-cheese tea canapes
directions: Cream butter, flour and cheese.
Add other ingredients and roll mixture into little balls.
Make a hole in the center of each and insert a stuffed green olive.
Place on a tray in the freezer until ready.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Serve with a good red wine and fruit cubes on picks.
Serves 6.

title: mocha torte
directions: Slice cake into 4 or 5 layers.
Cream butter.
Gradually add sifted confectioners sugar.
Add salt, vanilla and egg yolks; beat for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add baking chocolate, melted with coffee. Fold in egg whites.
Spread this mixture between layers; chill overnight.
Frost with whipped cream.

title: southern corn soup
directions: Combine corn and chicken broth in blender or food processor and puree.
In a 3-quart saucepan, combine butter and corn mixture and simmer slowly 5 minutes, stirring to keep corn from sticking to bottom of pan.
Add milk, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and add green chilies and chicken. Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove soup from heat and add cheese and baking soda (to prevent curdling).
Stir until melted.

title: cheddar ham chowder
directions: Bring water, potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper to a boil.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes, until tender.
Remove from heat.
In another pan, melt butter.
Blend in flour; add milk. Cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix these together.
Add corn and ham; heat thoroughly.

title: italian shrimp salad
directions: In medium saucepan, cook rice with water and Italian dressing until done. Refrigerate in a large bowl until cool.
Fold in peas, mushrooms, scallions, water chestnuts, olives, artichokes and mayonnaise.
Chill at least 24 hours.
Gently stir in shrimp or chicken.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Note: May use crunchy peanut butter for nuts.

title: aunt julia's crunchy granola
directions: Mix oats, wheat germ, coconut, cinnamon and brown sugar together.
Add oil, honey and vanilla; mix with hands.
Spread in 10 x 15-inch baking pan or jelly roll pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serve with milk.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large heavy saucepan, saute ground beef and onion lightly. Sprinkle with salt; add spaghetti sauce and remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes until macaroni is tender.
Stir once or twice.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: ninety minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°). Butter need not melt.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
On floured board, knead 2 to 3 minutes until smooth.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients, except ground chuck, to a boil.
Add raw ground chuck.
Simmer for 3 to 4 hours, stirring frequently.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and put in a baking dish. Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate glaze for cakes
directions: In a sauce pan heat the chocolate chips and butter over low heat until melted. This will need to be stirred often. Set aside. In a heavy saucepan mix whipping cream and corn syrup. Bring to a gentle boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in chocolate mixture. Cut your favorite cake and drizzle over top of each serving. Good on any cake.

title: suko
directions: In a deep pan, brown stew beef.
Add garlic salt to meat. Fill pan with water over half-full.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, sugar and lots of garlic salt.
Cook 2 1/2 hours.

title: boston cream dessert
directions: Make pudding as directed, then fold Cool Whip into mixture. Line the bottom of 9x13 pan with graham crackers, then add half of pudding mixture. Place a second layer of graham crackers over pudding mixture and then add remaining pudding. Top of with another layer of graham crackers and then pour melted chocolate frosting over crackers. Refrigerate overnight.
This is a favorite with all ages.

title: stella adamek's 3 bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables and combine.
Make dressing of sugar, vinegar, oil and seasonings.
Pour over beans.
Let set overnight. I add lima beans and chili beans.

title: skinny soup
directions: Cook cabbage, carrots and celery first (a few minutes).
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Brown sausage; add onion and garlic, then remaining ingredients.
When serving, sprinkle with cheese.

title: party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar, water, pineapple juice and ginger ale.

title: church potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and chopped onion in baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Cavender's seasoning.
Pat stick of butter over top; cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: steamed brown bread
directions: Step 1:
Sift flour (1/4 cup), salt and soda in bowl.
Add meal and whole wheat flour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in salted water for 10 minutes. Drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Put into 1-quart casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: holiday punch
directions: Chill the pineapple juice.
Mix with limeade.
Add a little sugar, if desired.
Add ginger ale and spoon in lime sherbet.

title: dilled broccoli
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over broccoli florets.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Cover the beans with water 2 inches above the beans.
Let stand overnight.
Drain just before using.
Place the ham hocks, 10 cups of the water, onions, bell peppers, bay leaves and seasonings in a 5 1/2-quart pan or large Dutch oven; stir well.
Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer until meat is fork-tender, about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove ham hocks from pan and set aside.
Add the drained beans and 4 cups of the water to the pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the remaining 2 cups water and simmer 30 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in the sausage and continue simmering until the beans start breaking up, about 35 minutes, scraping pan bottom fairly often.
(If beans start to scorch, do not stir.
Immediately remove from heat and change to another pot without scraping any scorched beans into the mixture.) Take meat off of ham hock bones and add to the pot; cook and stir 10 more minutes.

title: chicken alouette
directions: Unfold pastry sheets into 14 x 12-inch rectangle on floured surface.
Cut one sheet into 4 (7 x 6-inch) rectangles.
Cut second sheet into two.
Set aside.
Shape into oval (cut off corners). Spread evenly with cheese.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder in bowl.
Dough will be thin.
Pour dough in pan with butter.
Pour fruit over dough and this bakes around the fruit like a cake.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done in a 350° oven.

title: pineapple ice cream
directions: Combine evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Drain pineapple and reserve 1/3 cup juice.
Stir pineapple, juice and vanilla into milk mixture.
Mix well and spoon into hand turned or electric ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to instructions.
Let stand 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Yield: 1 quart.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add oil and beat 5 minutes more.
Sift dry ingredients and fold in.
Add nuts and apples. Use greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a pint jar until mixed well. Add catsup and mix.
Add vinegar and shake until well blended. Refrigerate for at least 1/2 hour prior to serving.
Shake again before serving.
Makes 1 pint.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots 5 minutes and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps 8 to 10 days.

title: versatile beef
directions: Cut meat in 1/4-inch pieces.
Brown in skillet and add onions, wine, salt, pepper and bouillon cubes.
Lower heat, cover and simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve this as you would any pot roast.

title: baked turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Put into large shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak the beans in water overnight.
The next morning, bring to a boil.
Add the baking soda.
Skim the foam and drain. Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Add the butter, sugar and salt. Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Empty cake mix and gelatin in bowl.
Mix and add oil.
Beat in eggs and 1 cup strawberries.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done. When cake is cool, ice with mix of 1 stick melted butter, powdered sugar and 1/2 cup strawberries.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Chop nuts and mix with coconut and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the cake mix as directed on box and pour over nuts and coconut. Mix cream cheese and margarine. Then add the sugar. Spoon this on top of cake mix. Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage and eggs casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Mix together beaten eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Break up bread; add cheese and sausage. Pour into greased glass baking pan, 11 x 7-inch.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: touch of heaven
directions: Chill milk, beaters and bowl well.
Whip milk stiff and fluffy or use Dream Whip.
Fold in extract and preserves.
Break cake into small pieces.
Place layer of cake in bottom of 2-quart casserole. Top with whipped mixture and repeat layers ending with whipped mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Wash, peel and quarter apples. Cook until soft in covered saucepan, using just enough water to keep from scorching. Stir occasionally during cooking. Break up quarters with fork and sweeten to taste with sugar.

title: fruit salad
directions: Soak bananas in pineapple juice for a few minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: praline cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Press into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and flour.
Blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Blend in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour over baked crumbs. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Loosen the rim and cool. Chill.
Pour a little maple syrup over and garnish with pecan halves.
Serves 12.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare lime Jell-O; pour into 8-inch glass square baking dish. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in crushed pineapple and chill until firm.
Gradually add mayonnaise to softened cream cheese; blend well.
Add nuts.
Spread over molded Jell-O.
Chill until firm.
Prepare strawberry Jell-O; cool.
Pour over cheese mixture and chill until firm.
Cut in squares.
Serve on lettuce and top with mayonnaise.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients (it should fizz).
Mix next five ingredients and set 1 cup aside.
Mix liquid and crumb mixtures together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with the cup of crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn-zucchini saute
directions: Saute zucchini in oil in large skillet or wok 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Add corn, garlic salt and Italian seasonings and saute 3 to 5 minutes until corn is tender-crisp.
Add pimiento.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Add to carrots and let set overnight.

title: tomato basil squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Using lightly floured dough roller, roll out pizza crust on a rectangle baking stone or pan. Sprinkle crust with 1 cup of the mozzarella cheese; set aside. Thinly slice tomatoes; arrange in a single layer over the mozzarella cheese on the crust. Mix all the remaining ingredients together in a mixing bowl. Then spread to cover evenly over the crust. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until top is golden brown and bubbly.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving portions; steam until tender.
Pat dry, refrigerate until time to fry.
If a large quantity is cooked, steam the day before.

title: slim jim sour cream
directions: Whiz in blender until smooth.
Chill until firm.

title: layered mixed vegetable salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
In a large bowl or 13 x 9-inch pan, layer lettuce and onion.
Spoon 1/2 cup mayonnaise evenly over top.
Layer chopped celery next.
Then layer diced green pepper.
Thaw and drain peas.
Layer peas.
Spread remaining mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle sugar and cheese.
Fry the bacon slices and then drain and crumble.
Add bacon over top.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
If desired, add drained water chestnuts.
Toss before serving.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Brown meat, onion and seasonings. Add 1 cup tomato sauce, 1/2 cup milk, egg, 1/4 cup catsup, 3/4 cup rice and 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stuff peppers. Place in roaster or Dutch oven. Cover with 2 cups tomato sauce, 3/4 cup catsup and 1/2 cup water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach salad
directions: In sauce pan mix sugar, jello and pineapple. Heat just until dissolved. Whisk in buttermilk, Cool Whip and pecans. Pour into 9x13 inch casserole dish. Chill.

title: spanish pizza
directions: Slice bread in about 1-inch slices.
Melt butter with garlic and butter bread.
Mix cheese, green chiles and mayonnaise. Spread on bread.
Bake in a 400° oven until bubbly.
Serve at once.
Great appetizers; you can't eat just one!

title: white potato medley
directions: Dice potatoes and soak in salted, ice water for at least 20 minutes.

In the meantime, saute the onion, bell pepper and garlic in the butter over low-medium heat for 20 minutes; don't brown. Drain the potatoes and add them to the onion and bell pepper; cook an additional 30 minutes or until potatoes are slightly browned and done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pickled beets
directions: Bring beets to a boil.
Tie spices in cheesecloth; add vinegar, sugar and boil 5 minutes.

title: slam enchilada casserole
directions: Layer with shells on bottom of 10 x 13-inch dish.
Spread beans, meat and cheeses.
Repeat and pour can of sauce over entire dish.
Top with remaining cheese, olives and peppers.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tins, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit lined cups; sprinkle with cheese.
Any other toppings may be added.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: country-style steak
directions: Brown steak in Crisco oil; when you turn your steak, add butter.
Lay steak out.
Mix flour in drippings; brown real brown and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add water and stir continually until you get consistency you want.
Place steak back in gravy and let simmer on medium for 30 minutes.

title: fried shrimp and okra
directions: In frying pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan. After washing the okra, cut into slices, taking off tops and bottoms.
Add onion, okra and bell pepper to pan; cook until tender, stirring constantly to keep from burning.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add in shrimp and cook until shrimp turn a bright pink, stirring often.
Serve as a side dish or over rice.

title: microwave okra creole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, heat onion and butter 3 1/2 to 5 minutes until onion is tender.
Add okra, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and pepper sauce.
Heat, covered, 22 to 25 minutes until vegetables are tender, stirring twice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: baklava
directions: Butter 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Line bottom with 2 sheets of phyllo.
Sprinkle with butter and chopped nuts.
Put on another layer of phyllo.
Sprinkle with melted butter and alternate layers of nuts and phyllo, sprinkling butter on each layer until about 1 1/2-inch thick.
Finish with 3 layers of phyllo.
With a sharp knife, cut through the first 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then increase to 400°.
Bake until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: can-can chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except noodles in a large skillet. Stir to mix.
Bring quickly to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 4 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove from heat; stir.
Serve with the noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate lime swirl pie
directions: Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Crush cookies and mix with melted margarine.
Press cookie mixture into pie pan to form a crust. Save 2 tablespoons cookie mixture for top.
Chill the pie crust. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add the lemon juice and sugar.
Let stand while you whip the chilled milk to a stiff froth.
Add jello and mix.
Continue whipping until stiff peaks are formed.
Mix in lemon rind and food coloring.
Pour into crust and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Chill until firm.

title: banana pie
directions: Combine in heavy pot first sugar and flour (blend them well), then add milk using a whisk.
Add egg yolks.
Turn on the stove burner, cook until thickened, continue stirring or it will lump up and stick.
Pour over bananas and vanilla wafers alternately layered.
Beat egg whites for topping or you can use whip cream for the topping.
If using egg whites you have to bake the pie until egg whites are golden brown.
Let cool and serve.

title: broccoli cheese quiche
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix cheese, flour and broccoli and put into pie shell.
Pour egg mixture over this and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: artichoke pita crisps
directions: Combine water, artichokes and celery in small saucepan. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Drain artichoke mixture well. Finely chop ham, green onions, olives and artichoke mixture in food processor.
Scrape into large bowl.
Puree cottage cheese in processor.
Add to bowl with mayonnaise and lemon juice.

title: 5-minute play dough
directions: In a medium saucepan put all ingredients.
Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture resembles mashed potatoes and comes away from sides of saucepan.
(If it is still sticky, it is cooked enough.)
Dump dough onto kneading surface and knead until all lumps are gone.

title: cinnamon cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray. Press one package crescent rolls on the bottom of the prepared pan.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine 3 cups flour, sugar, salt, soda and yeast.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry ingredients. Beat well. Stir in reserved flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 greased and cornmeal sprinkled loaf pans. Sprinkle tops with cornmeal. Cover and let rise 45 minutes. Bake in a 400° oven 25 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush
cookies.
Mix 3/4 of the cookies with the margarine (melted).
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Spread on cookie mixture.
Mix pudding and milk. Pour
over mixture;
add Cool Whip.
Top with remaining cookie crumbs.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and store in closed jar.
Use 3 teaspoons per cup of water.

title: baked halibut
directions: Dip steaks in salted milk, then in crushed cornflakes to coat thoroughly on both sides.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Drizzle tops of steaks with melted butter.
Add dash of paprika.
Bake in hot oven to 500° to 550° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cool as a cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add lemon juice. Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Blend in sour cream; add remaining ingredients.
Chill, soft set in 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed, drain and stir in other ingredients. Bake at 350° until casserole is dry, approximately 45 minutes.

title: potato dressing(grandma's recipe)
directions: Cook potatoes.
Mash with butter when cool.
Grind together onion, salt pork and crackers and add to potatoes.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and Bells seasoning.
Combine and stuff breast and tail cavities.
Bake turkey according to package directions.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water and set aside.
Cut shortening into the dry ingredients.
Stir in the buttermilk and the water-yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate or make into biscuits.
Let the biscuits rise slightly and bake in a 400° oven until lightly browned.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour batter into an 8-inch round cake pan coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Set oven slow at 300° to 325°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour into creamed mixture thoroughly; blend, using hands.
Press into oblong cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil.
Prick surface with fork.
Bake in preheated oven for about 1/2 hour, or until firm when pressed gently in center.
Should be only light brown.

title: mixed fruit casserole
directions: Layer pineapple pie filling, dry cake mix and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Do not stir.
Cover with butter slices. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 can French fried onions. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in a saucepan.
Stir until sugar and cornstarch are dissolved and blended.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until clear.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Cool thoroughly at room temperature.

title: chicken-n-spaghetti
directions: Saute seasonings in butter; add chicken pieces, Ro-Tel tomatoes, soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Add spaghetti and serve.

title: *hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Pour in pie crust.
Pour 1/2 jar pizza sauce over meat and mix in with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until crust begins to brown.
Remove from oven; cover with sliced cheese and bake until cheese melts and makes a golden crust.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Drain peas on paper towels.
Break lettuce in bowl.
Put green peppers, onion and peas in bowl.
Beat mayonnaise until fluffy. Spread over vegetables.
Sprinkle sugar over.
Sprinkle cheese over all.
Top with crisp bacon strips.
Cover tightly and chill for 8 hours.

title: spinach-mushroom salad
directions: In medium salad bowl, combine spinach with mushrooms and red pepper strips.
In small bowl, combine vinegar with water, sugar and mustard.
Add oil, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour dressing over salad and toss to coat.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs. Blend flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternately add milk and flour mixture to creamed ingredients.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour in a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan that has been greased.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: chile and cheese
directions: Cook chile on stove top when hot.
Put 1/2 jar of cheese in. Stir until melted.
Use dip for chips or on hot dogs.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat eggs; stir in pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Brown spareribs; drain grease.
Combine the rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over spareribs.
Simmer until tender, approximately 4 to 5 hours.
Remove spareribs from pan. We use the barbecue sauce over baked potatoes with sour cream on top.

title: chicken a la queen
directions: Saute macaroni, onion and green pepper until macaroni turns yellow.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix in chicken and broth.
Sprinkle cheese over top and simmer 5 minutes more.

title: easy chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then coat with breadcrumbs.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Cook chicken 10 minutes.
Set aside. Heat sauce in same skillet over medium heat, then return chicken to skillet.
Cover and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Top chicken with cheese and heat until melted.

title: cream cheese crescents
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll out and fold up in square 3 times. Then roll dough out thin.
Cut in 2-inch squares.
Put 1/2 teaspoon Smucker's apricot preserves in each.
Fold.
Bake on ungreased pan at 350°
for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: brown fudge squares
directions: Combine butter and cocoa in a small saucepan.
Heat just until margarine melts.
Set aside. Combine eggs and sugar in a large bowl, beating well. Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well. Add chocolate mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in pecans and/or chocolate chips. Bake in greased and floured 9 x 15-inch pan in a preheated oven at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked chicken
directions: Sprinkle 2/3 of onion soup in bottom of baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Place chicken in baking dish and add the mushroom soup and remainder of onion soup.
(I add a little water to mushroom soup.)
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender at 400°.

title: agnes lyons pepper relish
directions: Wash, clean and drain peppers.
Grind peppers fine.
Squeeze and drain again after grinding.
Grind onion.
While grinding onions, prepare a pot of boiling water.
Onions should have boiling water over them for 10 minutes.
Drain and put 3 trays of ice cubes to cool onions.
Put onions in pot and add all other ingredients except spices.
Put spices in cheesecloth and let it float in pickle after it starts to boil for 10 minutes.
Makes 12 pints.

title: sweet potato meringue pie
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and egg yolks; beat until combined.
Pour mixture into pastry shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 additional minutes or until set.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue over filling, sealing to edge of pastry.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely before serving.
Yield:
1 (10-inch) pie.

title: rotel spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in broth.
Add mushrooms and Ro-Tel, simmer.
Cook noodles, drain and mix all ingredients except cheese.
Add cheese last.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda, sugar, salt, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon; add the raisins.
In another bowl, beat together the eggs, oil, pumpkin and 1/3 cup of water.
Mix the pumpkin mixture into the flour mixture until combined.
Pour into buttered and floured loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let bread cool in pan for 15 minutes, then turn out.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple; mix pudding with pineapple juice.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Fold in marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: old family barbecue joes
directions: Cook together ground venison and onions until meat is browned and onion is transparent.
Drain.
Add ketchup, vinegar and spice.
Simmer over low heat for 2 1/2 hours, stirring and moving spice bag every half hour.
Remove bag and serve on buns or bread. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix everything together.
Cover and let set in refrigerator at least 3 hours.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all together for 1 minute at low speed then 3 minutes at high speed.
Add cherries and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes, thoroughly.
Cut thin slices from top of each tomato.
Remove pulp and turn upside-down to drain.
Stuff tomatoes with cheese mixture.
Garnish each top with a caper.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and gradually add sugar while mixing with mixer. Add eggs and enough milk to make a soft consistency.
Put in rectangular casserole dish.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Put in blender in order shown and blend until smooth.

title: apricot sauced sweet potatoes
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until apricots are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes. After cooked sweet potatoes are cooled, peel and cut into 6 or so slices (about 1/2-inch thick). Arrange in baking dish. Spread with pecans. Pour sauce over all. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are glazed. Baste once or twice while baking. Serve hot.

title: apple fritters
directions: Beat egg.
In a mixing bowl, combine the milk, egg and melted butter. Add the orange juice, rind, chopped apples (leave skin on) and vanilla.

title: festive ribbon fudge(choco-holics enjoy!!)
directions: Combine 3 cups sugar, 3/4 cup margarine and 2/3 cup evaporated milk in heavy 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full roaring boil. Continue boiling over medium heat 5 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add 1 jar marshmallow cream.
Beat until well blended. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Repeat with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate.
Spread over chocolate.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese-potato casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except 1/2 of the cheese; mix well and put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples in square baking dish.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add egg and mix until crumbly.
Pour over apples. Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Slit with knife.

title: lemon puff pudding(cake on top; lemon sauce on bottom.)
directions: Cream butter, 1/2 cup sugar and flour in a mixing bowl.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and milk. Add salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually beating in 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish; set dish in shallow pan, containing boiling water 1-inch deep.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool.

title: oatmeal cookies for a crowd(96 calories per serving)
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, sugar, pecan meat or walnuts, and oil. Blend and add water, milk, molasses, salt and vanilla to first mixture.
Add and mix raisins and walnuts well.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet; flatten.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: 1-2-3 peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to mix up well.

title: mexican supper
directions: In large container, add meat, beans, corn, sauce and tomatoes. Cook together about 5 to 7 minutes.
Have grated cheese and nacho chips.
Put chips in bowl.
Pour Mexican mix over; add cheese on top.
Serve green salad on side.
This makes a lot and freezes well.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Drain oysters.
In a buttered 1-quart casserole, place a layer of oysters, a layer of crackers, another layer of oysters and top with cracker crumbs.
Season.
Pour liquid from oysters or milk to measure 1/2 cup liquid over casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes (jackets on) until tender.
Drain and cool thoroughly.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Add onion, pickles and eggs and toss with mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot corn
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Add cheese and remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fruit cake(no bake - keep in refrigerator)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; heat in pan slowly until oleo and marshmallows are melted.
Mix dry ingredients.
Pour the melted ingredients over the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in oiled Bundt pan to chill and set.
Turn out and slice.
Store in refrigerator.
It also keeps well in freezer.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into casserole dish.

title: 7 can casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pull meat from bones.
Saute celery, onions and bell pepper in butter for long time, then set aside to cool.

title: box oven dinner pizza
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread crescent roll dough on bottom.
Pinch seams together to form crust.
Spread crust with pizza sauce, then cheese, meat and other toppings.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in box oven at 425° (until cheese is bubbly and crust is browned).

title: chicken supreme
directions: Lightly grease large Pyrex dish with margarine.
Line bottom with dried beef.
Open chicken cutlets and place small amount of butter in middle.
Roll cutlets and hold in place with 1/2 strip bacon.
Place on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour on top of chicken.
Bake slowly at 275° for approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: coffee cake
directions: Work first 5 ingredients until very fine crumbs.
Remove 2 cups of crumbs and set aside.
Add remaining crumbs to remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Divide batter into 3 (8-inch) greased round pans.
Top with remaining crumbs that were set aside. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over broccoli.
Place sliced water chestnuts over this.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Spread cheese and French fried onions over dish.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: chocolate chip coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease Bundt pan with shortening, then coat with sugar. Set aside. Mix together cake mix, pudding, eggs, oil and sour cream until well blended. Fold in coconut, walnuts and chocolate chip morsels. Pour into prepared Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with milk and salt.
Remove from heat and stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread in greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: mom's drop biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixing bowl, stir together flour, powder and salt.
Add shortening.
Stir until it looks like corn meal.
Add milk in parts until stiff.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Good with milk gravy.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix marshmallows and sour cream and let stand for several hours.
Mix remaining ingredients and blend with sour cream and marshmallows.

title: big-wheel burger skillet
directions: Mix together onion, ground beef, egg, rolled oats, salt, pepper and milk.
Mound in a 10-inch skillet.
With a wooden spoon handle, make 5 to 6 holes in mound.
Combine spaghetti sauce and kidney beans (with liquid).
Pour over and around meat mixture. Place over medium heat.
When hot, reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: martha washington
directions: Mix above by hand.
Shape into balls and refrigerate for 1 hour, until firm.
In top of double boiler, melt 12 ounce chocolate bits with 3/4 square of paraffin.
Get this real hot. Either at the stove or with chocolate in a cup, dip the candy balls by using a toothpick in each.
Put the candy immediately on a piece of wax paper.
Remove toothpick and put a drop of chocolate in each little hole.
Cool and eat.

title: grandma billie's marshmallows
directions: Place gelatin and 1/2 cup cold water in bowl; let stand while you put sugar, salt and 1/2 cup cold water in deep stew kettle. Boil to soft ball (235°). Pour gelatin mixture into the hot syrup. Beat it and beat it and beat it. Grease flat pan well on bottom and sides. Powder with powdered sugar and cornstarch. Pour mixture into pan and dust top; cool. Cut into squares and dust bowl on all sides.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, boiled eggs and onion; set aside.
Combine sugar, salt, mustard and flour; add eggs and vinegar.
Mix well; add water and stir until smooth.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Do not add celery and lettuce until ready to serve.
Sprinkle top with grated carrots.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes; dip in corn meal.
Put in skillet containing heated oil.
Fry until corn meal turns lightly brown.
Eat hot. Cook only what you can eat.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Stir together shrimp and cocktail sauce.
Place cream cheese on serving platter.
Pour shrimp/sauce mixture over cheese.
Place crackers around platter and serve.

title: cornbread sausage dressing
directions: Chop onions finely.
Brown sausage and drain.
Melt butter in a pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Stuff turkey neck and body cavity or can be cooked separately.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour a little chicken broth over.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Thaw dinner rolls and allow to rise in warm place until about double in size (approximately 3 hours).
Flatten roll dough (each one separately) on cutting board or plate.
Put 4 or 5 pieces of pepperoni and a generous amount of Mozzarella cheese.
Roll into a ball, keeping pepperoni and cheese inside.
Bake on cookie sheet according to directions on rolls or until golden brown (approximately 12 to 15 minutes).

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar until a soft ball forms when a drop is put in cold water.
Remove from flame. Add peanut butter and mix well. Pour into an 8 x 10-inch pan to cool.

title: microwave no fail fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in 10 x 8-inch dish.
Drop butter onto sugar mixture in 4 or 5 pieces.
Pour in milk.
Microwave 2 or 3 minutes on High or until bubbly.
Stir lightly.
Thoroughly stir in nuts and vanilla so nuts are evenly distributed.
Spread fudge evenly in dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour, then cut into squares.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in a casserole dish and add soup.
Add 1/2 of the onion rings.
Mix together well.
Sprinkle top with remaining onion rings and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sour cream, mayo and lemon juice. Add the broccoli, cauliflower, peas, cheese and onion; toss to coat. Refrigerate, covered, until chilled, at least 1 to 2 hours. Serve sprinkled with the bacon.

title: bacon-buttermilk dressing
directions: Prepare and chill this creamy mixture at least an hour in advance so the flavors can blend and mellow.

title: consumer union's* chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together sugars and softened margarine.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat until creamy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Gradually add dry ingredients to the other mixture.
Add the chocolate chips, mixing for 10 to 15 seconds. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 11 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: $100 coconut cake(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box for 9-inch cake layers. Cool and slice each layer. You will have 4 layers after sliced.

title: lillian hellman's pot roast
directions: Place roast in large pan.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over roast.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and place into a deep pie shell.
Top with another pie shell.
Bake in oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage until done and drain.
Add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix well about halfway through.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, onion and celery in 2 cups water until tender (do not drain).
Melt margarine. Add flour and bouillon.
When bubbly, add 2 1/2 cups water.
Combine pans until boils. Stir in cream.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: rhubarb jello salad
directions: Cook rhubarb, then add sugar to hot rhubarb and jello.
Stir well and then add pineapple.
Do not drain pineapple.
Mix well and put in a bowl to jell.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes and take insides out and set peel aside to fill later.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Put into potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chinese noodle salad with shrimp
directions: To the drained, cooked noodles, add the celery, shrimp, green onion, pepper and pimento.
Mix well.
Add enough Best Foods mayonnaise so that you can stir easily.
Add seasoning.
Decorate with olives and parsley.
This salad is better if it sits overnight.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mash egg yolks with mustard.
Add milk, sugar, Miracle Whip, vinegar, and salt.
Add chopped egg whites, celery, green peppers, and onions.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, add celery, onion and bell peppers and saute in grease.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz well while warming.
Combine cooked rice, sausage mixture and soup and cheese mixture all together in large casserole dish.
Cook in oven at 400° until hot and bubbly.

title: layered fruit salad
directions: Layer apples, apricots, pears, peaches and pineapple in a large bowl. Combine orange juice and lemon juice.
Pour over fruit. Spread cherry pie filling on top, then cover and chill 2 hours.
Arrange bananas over pie filling.
Sprinkle with coconut. Serve immediately.
Yields 14 to 16 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp and blend in blender.
Add all other ingredients and season with the seasonings to taste.

title: poor man's dinner
directions: In skillet, brown meat.
Season with pepper and garlic powder. In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, thinly layer the beef, potatoes and onion slices.
Pour soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt millie's broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C). Bring a pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook broccoli in the boiling water for 1 minute. Drain and set aside.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Slice potatoes in skillet with olive oil or canola oil for frying. Season to taste (pepper and salt). Add a pinch of sugar, if desired. Slice 1/2-inch pieces of green peppers, onions, mushrooms, kielbasa or Polish sausage on top. Fry until golden brown, turning once or twice.

title: "diet" dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in large glass casserole dish.
Spoon and spread pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of fruit.
Pour liquid Butter Buds on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown and looks "done".
Best served warm.

title: broccoli-mandarin salad
directions: *Scatter in shallow pan and bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until lightly toasted.
Don't let burn.

title: plain cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° until cake shrinks from sides of pan (greased 13 x 9-inch pan). Good for strawberry shortcake.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in small amount of hot fat until tender, but not brown.
Add meat and seasonings; brown lightly.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes while hot.
Add milk, egg and seasonings.
Drop in mounds over meat.
If you like, sprinkle potatoes with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry breeze pie
directions: Beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add Eagle Brand milk (condensed) and beat thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours until firm.
Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar until creamy.
Fold in peanut butter, milk and Cool Whip; mix well.
Let set about 4 hours in the refrigerator.

title: mixed nut bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter like a pie crust. Pat into 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Melt other ingredients until melted.
Add nuts and pour over cooled crust. Return to oven and bake for additional 10 to 15 minutes until bubbly.
Remove and cut into squares while still warm.

title: low-fat ranch dressing
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: honey dressing for fruit salad
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Refrigerate.
Shake well before adding to salad.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Stir pudding mix into pineapple juice.
Mix with fruit.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Make a sponge cake mixture by beating eggs and adding salt, sifted sugar and water.
Then add flour and baking powder.
Spread 1/4 c. butter on bottom of cake pan.
Add 1 c. brown sugar, 1 can shredded pineapple.
Pour the sponge cake mixture over this and bake in a moderate oven.
When done turn on a platter, cover with whipped cream.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Pour strawberries into pastry shell.
Mix water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Boil until clear and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add jello and let cool.
Pour over strawberries and let set in the refrigerator.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: In a large saucepan combine chicken broth, onion, tomato and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Place half of mixture in blender.
Cover and blend 30 to 60 seconds until smooth.
Pour in a bowl; repeat with remaining mixture.
Set aside.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a large iron frying pan.
Lay in pineapple slices with cherries in the middle.

title: low calorie fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together. Add vanilla or almond extract. Mix in egg yolks. Mix dry ingredients with butter mixture alternating with strawberries. Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks. Fold in egg whites and turn into a buttered loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes. Nice with coffee or tea.

title: fruit pasta salad
directions: Boil macaroni in 3 quarts boiling water.
Drain fruit (save juice).
Bring juice, sugar and flour almost to a boil.
Blend in 4 beaten eggs until thickened.
Cool macaroni and juice mixture.
Mix together.
Add in fruit and Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Add in more drained fruit as desired.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, cocoa and salt.
Put in oblong cake pan.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Put 3/4 cup oil in one hole, 1 teaspoon vanilla in one hole and the other hole vinegar.
Pour cold water over all.
Mix with fork.
Do not beat. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Prick each potato 3 times.
Arrange in a circle in microwave. Microwave on High 14 minutes.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes. While potatoes are cooling, cook bacon on High for 4 1/2 minutes. In a bowl, mix vinegar, cornstarch, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Stir in onion.
Microwave 8 minutes.
Cut potatoes in 1/2-inch pieces.
Add to broth mixture along with pimentos.
Toss to mix and coat.
Crumble bacon over top.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cook nuts in oil 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix vinegar, brown sugar, salt, cornstarch and soy sauce. Dredge chicken pieces in mixture.
Fry vegetables in oil. Remove them and fry chicken until sightly brown.
Return vegetables and broth.
Cook until vegetables and chicken are tender, stirring often. Add nuts just before finished cooking.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mash wafers and mix with fruit and nuts.
Add enough condensed milk to hold together.
After firm, sprinkle with whiskey.

title: banana brickle muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine the eggs, banana, oil and milk; mix well.
Add the flour, brown sugar and baking powder, stirring just until moistened.
Set aside 1/4 cup of the toffee bits; stir the remaining toffee bits into the batter.
Lightly grease 18 muffin cups or line them with paper baking cups.
Fill the cups 2/3 full with batter.
Sprinkle with the reserved toffee bits and bake for about 20 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of a muffin comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes in the pan on a wire rack.
Remove muffins and cool completely on the wire rack.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: barbecue hash
directions: Cook beef and pork covered with 2 or 3 inches of water and cook until meat is in small pieces.
Then add other ingredients and cook for 3 or 4 hours, stirring constantly.
Serves 5 to 8 persons.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs until fluffy.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Fold in bread cubes.
Bake uncovered in a greased casserole for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: tippsy squire
directions: Into a large Tupperware bowl with lid, break pound cake into small pieces.
Add nuts, apricots and bourbon.
Into a heavy saucepan, add eggs, milk and sugar.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture will coat a wooden spoon.
Pour cooked mixture over pound cake, apricots, nuts and bourbon.
Stir until well mixed.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 4 hours or longer. When ready to serve, place serving in a parfait glass; top with whipped cream and a maraschino cherry.

title: easy skillet potatoes
directions: In a large skillet over medium flame, cook onion slices in melted butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove the cooked onion to a plate and keep warm for later use.
Add potatoes and salt to the remaining butter in skillet; cover and cook over medium flame until potatoes are golden brown.
Add onions to potatoes and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and cook until cheese melts.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: company chicken
directions: Remove skin and bones from breast.
Halve them.
Wrap a piece of bacon around each piece of chicken.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Line bottom of pan with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken on beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until chicken is thoroughly done. Serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes on 350°.

title: homemade hot chocolate mix
directions: In a large bowl stir together the cocoa, sugar, powdered milk, non-dairy creamer and salt.
Store in air tight containers or glass jars.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix sugar, salt and vinegar.
Pour over cucumber slices and chill for 4 hours.
Keep several days in refrigerator.

title: dip
directions: Mix beef, taco seasoning, tomatoes and cheese.
Mix well.
If you like it warm, heat in microwave for a few seconds and keep warm in small crock-pot.

title: mahogany pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Combine sour cream and baking soda. Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in vanilla.
Beat egg whites; fold into batter.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together the ground beef, corn flakes, egg, sweet relish, mustard and onion.
Roll into balls and place in baking dish. Bake at 350° until half way done; cover with tomato soup and continue cooking until done.
Serve with cooked spaghetti.

title: willie's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix peanut butter, graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine together.
Mix well!
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave and spread over mixture.
Let set at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
Cut in squares.

title: cream cherry pie
directions: Cook milk, flour, egg yolks, sugar and salt until mixture starts to thicken. Add margarine, marshmallows and vanilla.
Pour into cooked crust.
Then add on top already prepared pie cherries. Top with meringue and bake until lightly brown.
Let set.

title: barbecue(spicy-sweet)
directions: Cook roast until it falls apart.
Cool and tear apart.
Place in a large pot.
Mix all other ingredients and add to meat. Simmer at least 40 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix.
Place in jar and store in refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and salt until mixture threads or 290° to 300°.
Add butter and peanuts. Cook until mixture turns light brown in color. Add soda. Pour a thin layer in a pan to cool.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Sift flour in a tray or long dish. Make a hole in the middle of the flour with your hands.
Put the potatoes in the hole.
Add Crisco, baking powder, water and salt. Mix by hand like you would other biscuits.
Pinch off dough in biscuit size pieces.
Roll in floured hand until smooth.
Place in greased biscuit pan and bake in oven at 475° until done. Serve warm with butter.
Makes about 24.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cover bottom of iron skillet with grease.
Add mixture to pan.
Heat on burner before putting in oven.
Cook 25-30 minutes at 400 degrees.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Whisk together mayo, sour cream, mustard, lemon juice and sugar.
Core and quarter the cabbage.
Cut quarters into 1/8-inch julienne to make approximately 6 cups.
Peel carrots and grate coarsely.
Wash and core apples; grate coarsely.
Combine cabbage, carrots and apples.
Add dressing and toss thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight to let slaw marinate.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch the gelatin and boiling water until dissolved. Add pineapple (undrained) and blueberry pie filling. Stir and let set. Mix sour cream with cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Do not overbeat. Spread on top of gelatin mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
In a medium size bowl, mix flour with baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, beat margarine, peanut butter and both sugars until creamy.
Add eggs; blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and cinnamon mixture; blend well.
Fold in oatmeal and raisins.

title: italian cheesecake
directions: Combine ingredients in order in baking dish (glass or Corning Ware).
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, until top begins to turn light brown.
Bake in glass or Corning Ware dish, 13 x 8 3/4-inch.

title: roasted venison(hind quarter)
directions: Clean all fat from meat.
Poke holes in meat.
Place meat in a roasting pan; cover with your favorite oil based salad dressing (Italian, red wine and vinegar, Caesar, etc.).
Slice 2 large onions and add to pan.
Marinate for 2 to 12 hours.
Preheat oven to 300°; cook meat (covered) at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is pulling from the bone.
Do not overcook.
Drippings make good stock for gravy.
Just add flour and water, mixed.
Will feed 12 to 15 people.

title: date bars
directions: Cut dates up and put warm water over them.
Let stand until you have the rest mixed together.
Then drain well and throw away the water.
Add dates to other mixture and bake in a greased and floured 11 x 7 x 1/4-inch pan until done.
Cool.
Cut into bars and roll in powdered sugar.
These require no shortening!

title: caramel pecan coffee cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, cream and 1/4 cup melted butter in angel food pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in bowl or on waxed paper.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine 1 cup meal, salt and soda; mix in bowl.
Add eggs, milk, corn and bacon grease.
Stir until smooth; set aside. Saute beef and sausage; drain.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cornmeal in greased skillet and heat.
Pour half of batter in the skillet; sprinkle with cheese, ground beef, sausage and onion, then pepper. Pour remaining batter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let stand in skillet about 10 minutes.

title: croutons
directions: Cut bread slices in 1/2-inch cubes.
Bake on cookie sheet until dry.
You can sprinkle with cheese, garlic or herbs after drizzling with butter (if so desired).
Bake at 225° about 2 hours.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix in bowl.
Bake for 15 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Can brown bread crumbs in butter.
Put cheese on top.

title: chicken breasts with bulgur wheat
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven or casserole, combine all ingredients in order given.
Stir to combine.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O and add the pie filling.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan. Set in refrigerator.
Allow it to set for at least 4 hours. Combine the sour cream and powdered sugar.
Spread over set Jell-O.
Serve after chilled.

title: pesto pizza
directions: Spread pesto sauce over pizza shell.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Saute in olive oil the cubed tofu, sliced and ringed or chopped onions, sliced mushrooms and about 2 tablespoons sesame seed.
Add to top of pizza.
Add cut up artichoke hearts, chopped or torn spinach, pine nuts (worth the expense), pineapple (optional) and sliced tomatoes.
Top with Parmesan cheese and crumbled Feta cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spiced apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange apples in ungreased square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Stir together oats, brown sugar and cinnamon in medium bowl.
Cut in margarine.
Stir in cereal.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: date cake
directions: Cut dates into small pieces. Place in bowl. Sprinkle soda over dates. Pour boiling water over dates and let stand until cool. Beat together eggs, oil, sweetener and vanilla. Add flour, salt and baking powder. Add cooled date mixture and nuts. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite sized pieces.
Toss lightly.
Add remaining ingredients, after mixing, over vegetables.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: laverne's quick fruit cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour in oblong pan.
Don't stir. Pour fruit over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt margarine, mince garlic and simmer together 3 minutes. Add shrimp and all other ingredients except cornstarch mixture. Cook about 10 minutes on low flame.
Then add cornstarch and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: crusty beef, cheese and noodle casserole
directions: Heat oil; add onion and cook until golden.
Add meat and cook until meat loses its red color.
Add mushroom sauce and heat. Arrange in casserole, half of noodles, half of sauce and half of cheese.
Make another layer of noodles.
Add sauce and top with cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour, until top is nicely browned.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 25 minutes.

title: okra gumbo
directions: May have to add more water.
Boil until cooked.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all juice from first 2 ingredients.
Put marshmallows in large bowl.
Pour fruit over; let stand for 1 hour.
Fold in sour cream.
Let stand overnight.

title: microwave broccoli and cauliflower cheese sauce
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients 2 minutes on High, stirring after each minute.
Add milk gradually.
Microwave 4 minutes, stirring after each minute.
When sauce is thick, add cheese slices and blend in.
Pour over vegetables.

title: twisted river ranch cabbage salad
directions: Poach chicken; let cool and chop.
Toast sesame seed.
Break up noodles (do not cook).
Add cabbage, onions, sesame seed and chicken.

title: old fashion cream pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Keep heat on medium.
Add sugar and stir.
Add cornstarch and stir.
Add milk and stir until it boils.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour immediately into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: baked lemon catfish
directions: Place fish on foil.
In skillet, melt oleo and saute celery, carrots and onions.
Spread over fish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Seal foil well.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes, depending on thickness of fish. Contains 322 calories, 26 grams fat, 14 grams carbohydrates, 106 mg cholesterol and 298 mg sodium.

title: baked steak
directions: Salt and pepper the round steak and brown on both sides. Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add onions, green peppers, mushroom soup and water.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans, in large bowl.
When thoroughly mixed, add pecans; stir to coat well.
Spread peanuts on foil covered cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 35 minutes. Stir once or twice to crisp and dry evenly.

title: loaf cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Bake 2 hours at 300° in a greased tube pan.
Cool. Great plain or topped with fresh strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients
in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and salad oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not beat. Stir in pineapple, vanilla, nuts and bananas.
Spoon batter into three 9-inch cake pans. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove and cool thoroughly. Spread frosting between layers and on top of cake.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Prepare Italian dressing according to directions, but substitute red wine vinegar instead of apple cider vinegar. Marinate chicken breasts in dressing.
Bake at 450° until chicken is done.

title: vegetable kabobs
directions: Place broccoli and cauliflower in water in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Microcook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 5 minutes.
Gently stir in potatoes, tomatoes (quartered) and wedged onions.
Cover; cook 4 to 6 minutes or until nearly tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
Put cooked veggies on skewer.
Add uncooked zucchini between veggies.
Brush with salad dressing and grill 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with dressing as they are turned.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Put rhubarb in pan.
Cover with water and cook 5 minutes. Drain.
Mix egg yolks, sugar, flour, cream and butter well.
Add rhubarb and cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Combine soups, water, butter and mushrooms.
Heat and stir over moderate heat.
When warm, blend.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and set aside.
To remaining add rice and stir.
Pour mixture into 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour the reserved 1 cup soup mixture over chicken.
Place in a 325° oven.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Add ground beef to water in a 4-quart pot; stir until beef separates into a fine texture.
Boil slowly for 1/2 hour.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend, bringing to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Last hour may cover, if desired consistency is reached (will not be as thick as conventional chili).
May refrigerate overnight and skim fat from top before reheating.
Serve over spaghetti with Cheddar cheese. (May also add chopped onions, if to your taste.)

title: stuffed new potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes on a medium heat till soft and cool in fridge . Combine the rest of the ingredients together.
Cut cooled potatoes in half.
With a melon scoop or a small spoon scoop out a bit of potato and discard.
Spoon some of the mixture into the potato, about a Tbsp.
Bake 375° 15-20 minutes.
Serve immediately.
If any of the mixture left save in the fridge.
It works great on top of a baked potato!

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Use a large glass bowl, if available.
Layer lettuce in bottom of bowl.
Add a layer of sliced eggs, standing some up on the side of bowl.
Add a layer of chopped onions, celery and pepper.
Add another layer of lettuce.
Add a layer of English peas.
Add a layer of chopped tomatoes.
Add a layer of shredded cheese. Spread a layer of mayonnaise over the top of it all, sealing to the edge of the bowl.
Sprinkle with a layer of bacon bits.
Cover and let set overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: cucumber dill dip
