directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers in red or green bell pepper.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: fried rice
directions: Pour oil in a large frying pan, add chopped onion and garlic; brown.
Add hamburger; brown.
Add eggs and scramble.
Add rice and soy sauce until rice turns light brown in color.
Add drained shrimp.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cook chicken and take off bone.
Cook noodles.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Stir together.
Add a little sweet milk.
Top with herb stuffing or toasted bread crumbs. Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn and beans or broccoli.
Mix together with above ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 300° to 350°.
Ovens may vary.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown meat with onions in a skillet.
Place in crock-pot (low) with all other ingredients except potatoes.
Cook 3 hours (up to 6 hours on low).
Add potatoes approximately 45 minutes prior to being served.
To thicken, add a little flour and water (in a shaker mix) to mixture.
The longer you can let simmer, the better. (Don't forget the corn bread!)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together. Put into casserole dish and sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Dot top of casserole with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: easy trifle
directions: Spread half the ladyfingers with preserves.
Top with remaining halves.
Line sides and bottom of 5 cup 3-inch deep serving dish with ladyfingers.
Moisten with sherry (or brandy, etc.).
Fold whipped cream into eggnog until well blended.
Pour carefully in center of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with whipped cream, preserves and almonds is additional and optional.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a buttered dish. Crumble approximately 15 Ritz crackers and sprinkle on top. Dab with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: twenty-four hour fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit and set aside.
Mix together beaten egg yolks, pineapple juice, flour and sugar.
Cook until thick, then let cool.
Add cherries to cooked mixture. Pour mixture over pineapple and fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.
Add bananas, marshmallows and whipped topping.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Drain cooked, frozen peas or canned peas.
If frozen peas are used, cook in 1/2 cup boiling, salted water.
Put 1 cupful in a buttered baking dish.

title: wimpies
directions: Saute onion and celery (chopped) in small amount of oil.
Add hamburg and brown.
Add ketchup, Worcestershire and chili sauce. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer slowly (low heat) for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: turkey divan
directions: Heat margarine in 1-quart saucepan over low heat until melted. Stir in flour and nutmeg.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Stir in 1/2 cup cheese and the apple juice.

title: chocolate chip cookie pie
directions: Cream margarine in small mixer bowl.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour; add to butter/egg mixture. Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool for 1 hour and serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: brussels sprouts supreme
directions: Place Brussels sprouts, celery, and a small amount of water in a saucepan; cover and cook for 8 minutes or until crisp-tender. Meanwhile, in another saucepan, melt butter.
Stir flour until smooth.
Gradually add milk; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Add cheese, salt, and cayenne if desired; stir until cheese is melted.
Drain sprouts and celery; top with cheese sauce.
Yield:
4-6 servings.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: best ever salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, along with cream cheese and marshmallows; beat until smooth.
When semi-thickened, add nuts, pineapple and whipped cream.
Nuts and pineapple may be left out.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: In a large kettle,
bring 4-inches of water to boiling. Immerse tomatoes in boiling water
for
minute.	Drain in a colander.
Peel, seed and
chop tomatoes.
(You should have 10 cups.)

title: cold fruit salad
directions: Mix together and put in freezer until it's like slush.

title: campfire eclairs
directions: You will need 1/2-inch or larger 18-inch wooden dowels and 1 campfire.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix meat and the next 4 ingredients to make meat balls.
Form into balls and saute in butter.
Heat pizza sauce and jelly in pot until jelly melts and sauce is hot.
Add meat balls; cook and serve.
Makes 40 meat balls.

title: snicker's cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour half batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels with margarine and milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring frequently.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon remaining cake batter over caramel layer.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.
Increase temperature to 300° and bake 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
16 to 20 servings.

title: deep-fried okra
directions: Wash okra and slice into 1/4 inch wheels.
Salt well, then sprinkle hush puppy mix (about 1/2 cup) over okra to coat.
Place okra in a colander and run cold water over to wet.
Mix remaining hush puppy mix with flour and sugar in a large bowl with a tight fitting lid.
Take the okra from the colander, place into mixture, cover and shake until okra is completely coated.
Shake excess mixture from okra and fry in oil until golden brown.
Oil needs to be hot when you put the okra in it.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cut strawberries into pie shells until approximately 1/2 full. Mix water, sugar and cornstarch. Cook on medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Add small box jello. Mix well. Pour over strawberries into pie shell. Let completely cool until set. Cover with Cool Whip and serve.

title: cathedral candy(makes 4 rolls)
directions: Melt chocolate chips with butter.
Beat eggs and vanilla. Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix marshmallows with nuts. Pour chocolate mixture on marshmallows.
Mix together.
Cut 4 (1 foot) pieces of foil.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on foil. Place some marshmallow mixture on foil.
Roll up.
Freeze 2 hours. Slice.

title: blueberry tea cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In medium bowl, with wooden spoon, beat egg; gradually beat in 2/3 cup sugar.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Fold in blueberries.

title: 4 layer marshmallow bars
directions: Mix cake, margarine and water until blended.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
(Use Pam or grease pan if not a nonstick pan.) Bake until done or 22 to 24 minutes at 375°.
Layer marshmallows, then candies and nuts on baked cake.
Put back in oven 2 to 3 minutes or until marshmallows are melted.

title: mom's burritos
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Pour off grease. Add 1 package taco seasoning and 1 taco seasoning package of water.
Add refried beans and chiles.
Mix well and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Fill tortillas with meat mixture, Cheddar cheese and other condiments as desired.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in a large bowl:
lettuce, 2 teaspoons sugar, cauliflower, chopped onion, 2 teaspoons sugar, bacon, 2 teaspoons sugar.
Cover top of salad with mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese. Cover and chill.

title: angel hair pasta with fresh tomatoes
directions: Heat oil in medium saucepan.
Add zucchini, squash and garlic; cook for 3 minutes; Add tomatoes and basil; cook for 5 minutes or until hot and slightly thickened.
Toss pasta with sauce.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Boil mushrooms until tender (about 1/2 hour).
Remove stems; snip into small pieces.
Combine stems with remaining ingredients. Roll mixture into small balls and place inside caps.
Place on greased (Pam) baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix eggs and water 3 to 5 minutes with mixer.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Mix again.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, then add dry ingredients.
Grease and flour 10 to 15-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Unroll when cool and spread with favorite jelly. Remove towel and roll back up.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter; add beaten eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: ham delights
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend margarine, mustard, onion, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread top and bottom of party rolls with the mixture.
Place boiled ham and Swiss cheese on rolls.
Cut into squares and wrap in foil.
Bake for 10 minutes. Great party or shower food!
Freezes well!

title: thanksgiving day salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool.
Add strawberries and cranberry sauce.
Stir.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2-quart ring mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Put on lettuce leaves to serve.

title: sweet cucumber and dill salad
directions: Place cucumber slices in colander; sprinkle with salt.
Toss. Let drain for 15 minutes.
Combine vinegar, sugar and cayenne pepper.
Pat cucumber slices dry and toss with dressing and dill. Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Put can of cherry pie filling, spread evenly, in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Next, put can of pineapple; spread this evenly over cherries.
Next, put box of dry cake mix on top of pineapple; spread evenly.
Next, cut butter into patties, then drop over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked luncheon meat
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients; spread on top of luncheon meat that has been sliced and placed in a casserole dish.
Cover and heat for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove cover and let cook 10 minutes longer.

title: mexican dip
directions: Peel avocados; take seed out and mash.
Add lemon juice; mix well.
Place into pizza pan.
Mix the sour cream, garlic powder and salt; pour on top of avocados.
Mix up picante sauce; pour on top of sour cream mixture.
Add chopped peppers, onions, black olives and cheese to top.
Cover; chill several hours.
Serve with Fritos.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Crush 1 roll Ritz crackers; mix with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind raw cranberries, orange and apple quarters.
Leave the peelings on.
Mix well with sugar and allow to stand 24 hours before serving.

title: texas red
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Great over spaghetti or macaroni.

title: real fruit cake
directions: Chop or cut fine, all fruit and nuts; mix well and combine with old fashion pound cake dough, using 10 eggs to corresponding proportions.
This recipe makes two nice cakes, unexcelled.

title: easy lemon pound cake
directions: Mix together until well blended (with electric mixer, about 2 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.
After baking, turn onto plate and pour sugar glaze over slightly warm cake.

title: carita's banana pudding(quick and easy)
directions: Mix instant pudding according to box directions.
Set aside while you slice the bananas; pudding will thicken slightly.
Add bananas and vanilla wafers to pudding; stir to mix.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate; garnish with extra vanilla wafers or banana slices.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine bread, milk and cream in a bowl. Beat eggs with sugar; add to bread. Add vanilla, spices, butter and raisins. Butter baking dish. Set in shallow pan. Pour hot water in pan (1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Add pineapple with juice and marshmallows.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: light alfredo sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Pour into a small saucepan; cook sauce over low heat, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
2 3/4 cups.
Serve over pasta.

title: crescent pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out flat on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on rolls.
Press onto cheese spread small bite size pieces of celery, broccoli, carrot, cauliflower or whatever vegetables you want.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in small amount of fat; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: flubber(non-edible, but kids love it!)
directions: You will also need 2 large bowls, measuring cups, strainer, measuring spoons and a spatula.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and mash very fine.
Add Cheez Whiz, Velveeta cheese and chopped chestnuts.
Sprinkle top of mixture with grated cheese and serve warm.

title: baked beans(for 75 people)
directions: Pour all ingredients into a large container or electric oven and mix well.
Heat at 375° until bubbly on sides.
Then reduce heat to 250° and cook 1 1/2 hours more.
Stir frequently.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain and add taco seasoning according to package directions.
Set aside to cool.
Tear lettuce into large bowl; add cheese, tomatoes and cooled meat.
In separate bowl, combine taco sauce and mayonnaise.
Pour over lettuce mixture and toss until all is coated.
Serve and sprinkle crushed Doritos over top.

title: apple butter bars
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt in a large bowl. Add oats and sugar. Stir in butter and mix well. Press half of mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan; top with apple butter. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture; press gently with a spoon. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until browned. Cool. Cut into bars. Yield: 3 dozen bars.

title: noodle and hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Heat soups and milk.
Add noodles and meat mixture.
Pour into buttered baking dish and bake at 350° until the noodles are done, about 1 hour.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Mix mayo, pimento, Worcestershire, mustard and 1/2 cheese in blender until smooth.
Add rest of cheese.
Blend until smooth.

title: luncheon meat-hot dish
directions: Stir in chow mein noodles.
Bake in a covered dish for 45 minutes at 375°.
Cube bread slices; fry in butter.
Pour over the top 15 minutes before done and put back in oven with cover off for 10 to 15 minutes, until crisp.
This freezes well.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: *Make your own cornbread or use 2 packages Korn Kits and mix according to directions and bake.
Let cool.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Place eggs and brown sugar in top of double boiler.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and add pecans.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle top with powdered sugar and cut in squares.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Cook broth with tomato (break up) and bay leaf.
Add clams and shrimp.
Add crab and fish just to cook.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling salted water, drain.
Melt butter, blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth all at once, cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in whipping cream.
Place broccoli crosswise in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add half of the sauce.
Top with chicken pieces.
To remaining sauce, add Parmesan cheese; pour over chicken and sprinkle with extra Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Then broil just until sauce is golden.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except butterscotch chips.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Pour the butterscotch chips on top of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: lexington-style sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan and bring to a simmer, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, stirring until the sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and let stand until cool.
(Make tangy and hot to suit your taste.)

title: grilled onions
directions: Peel onions and cut in half.
Place on a sheet of foil large enough to cover onion.
Sprinkle generously with Tony's and lemon pepper (about 1 teaspoon each) over onion.
Add about 1 teaspoon of oleo on top of onion and wrap in foil.
(It should look like a large Hershey's Kiss.)
Grill or bake in oven for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: apple hill cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, diced apples, walnuts and raisins. Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda.
Add flour mixture to apple mixture.
Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.
Dab each piece with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken and basil pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions, except omit any oil and use 1/4 teaspoon salt. Drain pasta. Rinse with cold water; drain. Meanwhile, rinse chicken and pat dry with paper towels. Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces. Spray an unheated large skillet with nonstick coating. Preheat over medium-high heat. Add the chicken and stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Sprinkle with the salt and pepper. Remove chicken from heat. In a large mixing bowl, toss together cooked macaroni, chicken, tomatoes, zucchini or summer squash and green onions. Drizzle with salad dressing. Sprinkle with basil. Toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to 6 hours. Toss salad before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix sour cream and egg together.
Next add corn and corn bread mix to sour cream.
Put in casserole and top with butter.
Cut in small squares.
Cook for 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: pork chops a la vineyards
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 5 minutes. Add cornstarch mixture to thicken.
When thickened, add parsley and paprika.
Bake pork chops 30 minutes at 450°.
Remove chops to another dish.
Add sauce and bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice without stirring until tender.
Raisins boiled with the rice is an improvement in which case add little more water. Beat eggs, sugar, milk, salt, butter, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add this mixture to rice.
Place in moderate oven.
Bake slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Open oven door every half hour and with spoon break the crust and stir up the rice.
Be sure to bake very slowly.
It will dry.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water 5 minutes and chill. Dissolve jello in boiling water then add cold water.When it begins to congeal add nuts, celery and pineapple. Chill cranberry mixture and let congeal.

title: shortbread
directions: Melt butter until soft.
Add vanilla and stir, combine all other ingredients.
Mix with your hands.
Roll dough on floured surface into medium size balls.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: meatballs in mushroom sauce with noodles
directions: Bring water and salt for noodles to boil.
In medium bowl, combine stuffing, onions and milk.
When soft, add beef, egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix until combined.
Shape into 2 dozen meatballs.
Add noodles to boiling water.

title: texas hot sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in a large kettle.
Pour off fat.
Place soup into kettle; add about one soup can of water, then add all the other ingredients.
Mix well; bring to a boil, then simmer slowly until mixture thickens, about 2 hours.
If desired, a tablespoon or two of flour dissolved in a small amount of water may be added near the end of the cooking time.
Remove bay leaves before serving; serve over grilled hot dogs.
First spread mustard over dog, then add chopped onions and top with sauce.

title: washday mini reubens
directions: Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into triangles. Place one slice corn beef across wide end of triangle. Spread 2 tbsp sauerkraut on corned beef. Top with two strips of Swiss cheese. Add dab of Thousand Island dressings. Roll up, beginning at wide end of triangle. Preheat oven to 375° while arranging sandwiches on an un-greased baking sheet. Put baking sheet into oven for 10-15 minutes. Check sandwiches. Do they look brown? Good! Transfer to a large plate plate and eat all eight!

title: gazpacho
directions: Divide juice between 4 bowls.
Do same with all vegetables. Chill until serving time.
Just before serving, swirl 1 ounce sour cream into each serving.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: old fashioned stew
directions: In Dutch oven, combine stew, 1 1/2 cups water, salt, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, pepper and bay leaf. Cover and cook on low heat about 20 minutes. Add carrots and potatoes until tender. Remove bay leaf. Blend flour with 1/2 cup water. Stir slowly into hot liquid. Cook and stir until thickened. Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until soft.
Mix in separate bowl mayonnaise, soup, onion, cheese and eggs.
Pour over broccoli in casserole pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and bananas, then combined dry ingredients. Fold nuts and bake in two smaller or one large loaf pan.
The pans should be one-half full. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients:
salt, baking powder and spices.
Add eggs, oats, flour and raisins.
Spoon teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes (do not overbake).
Soft and chewy.

title: classic green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper. Add beans and 1/2 can of onions. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Top with remaining onions. Bake 5 more minutes. Recipe can be doubled.

title: seafood mold
directions: Mix liquids and spices.
Add everything else.
Mix well. Place in mold.
Mold will be firm in 2 hours in refrigerator.
If placed in individual molds will firm up in approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss to mix well. Cover and chill for at least 2 hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apricot balls
directions: Grind or dice apricots.
Add coconut and milk.
Shape into balls. Melt together Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip apricot balls in chocolate mixture and put on waxed paper to cool.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt
butter in heavy saucepan.
Mix in flour, salt and pepper.
Add grated cheese and as it begins to melt; add milk. Cook
until
thick.
Place
of
bread crumbs in bottom of casserole.
Put
remaining
ingredients
in
layers, beginning with
asparagus,
sliced
eggs, pimentos, mushrooms, then pour over part
of
sauce.
Make another layer and top with crumbs. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chinese goulash
directions: Brown ground beef. Then add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into casserole dish. Bake in a 350° oven 1 1/2 hours or until rice is cooked.

title: mexican style eggs
directions: Whisk together eggs, egg whites, salt and pepper in a bowl. Heat butter in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, tomato, jalapenos and cilantro.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes until onion is clear.
Add egg mixture to skillet.
Cook, stirring, until desired consistency, 4 to 6 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: coke salad
directions: Heat Coke to melt jello.
Add rest of ingredients and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Sausage and cheese need to be at room temperature.
Mash sausage.
Sprinkle cheese and flour in a little at a time.
Put on greased cookie sheets.
Cook at 400° for 12 minutes.
Turn and cook 10 to 12 minutes longer.
To keep warm, put in crock-pot on low heat.
Great for parties.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can pork and beans into bottom of greased casserole. Combine sugar and mustard; sprinkle half of mixture over beans. Sprinkle the rest of sugar-mustard, chopped bacon and catsup over beans.
Or, if you prefer, you may combine all of the ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, in slow oven (325°) for 2 1/2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: crabmeat and shrimp dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in casserole dish at 325° to 350° until bubbly.
Serve hot with chips, crackers or party breads.

title: lazy woman's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Pour in an 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix dry ingredients and milk.
Mix well.
Pour over melted butter in baking dish.
Pour fruit over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: embelle's squash pie
directions: Saute the onion and pepper in the butter. Add to the cooked and mashed squash.
Add the egg.
Salt and pepper to taste.
If too soupy, crumble saltines until suitable. Bake at 350° until set.

title: spinach squares
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Combine next 9 ingredients.
Add spinach, rice and cheese.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: company carrots
directions: Cook the whole carrots in boiling, salted water until tender. Reserve 1/4 cup of the cooking liquid.
Drain carrots; cut lengthwise into narrow strips and arrange in shallow baking dish (8 or 9-inch square).
Combine reserved cooking liquid with mayonnaise, onion, horseradish sauce and salt and pepper.
If desired, at this point, the carrots and sauce may be refrigerated.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Grate the sharp cheese.
Mix with the pie crust mix.
This blends better if grated cheese is room temperature.
Add pepper to suit.
Chopped nuts optional.
If needed, add small amounts of butter melted to form ball of dough.
Shape into long roll the size of a half dollar.
Refrigerate or freeze.
When ready, slice and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 425° to 450° until lightly browned, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
(Do not use pie crust sticks.)

title: taco salad *
directions: In a 10-inch deep-dish, nonmetal pie pan (a glass quiche plate is perfect), spread the beans evenly over the bottom.
Sprinkle the cheese over the beans.
Microwave for 30 seconds on High or until the cheese melts.
Spread the guacamole over the cheese, then a thin layer of the salsa.
Gently spread the yogurt over the salsa.
Arrange the tomatoes in a ring around the outer edge of the pie pan.
Make an inner ring by sprinkling the chopped green onions inside the tomato ring.
Serve with nacho chips on the side for dipping.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil together brown sugar, syrup, molasses and margarine for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring often.
Remove from heat and add soda. Have popcorn and peanuts in deep pan (I use a roaster) and pour syrup mixture over popcorn and nuts.
Mix and put in oven at 250°. Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and put on waxed paper to cool.
Store in a tightly closed container.

title: golden rice salad
directions: Blend together salad oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over hot rice; toss and set aside to cool.
Add remaining ingredients and toss.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce leaf and garnish with extra sliced eggs.
Makes 8 one cup servings.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Partially cook broccoli.
Drain.
Saute celery and onion in butter until tender.
Combine broccoli, celery, onion, cheese, soup and rice in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Blend butter, egg and sugar.
Dissolve baking soda in teaspoon water and add to the mixture.
Add salt, bananas, flour and nuts. Mix and pour in a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour (bake 15 minutes longer if needed).

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden, about 20 minutes.
Add flour and cook about 5 minutes, stirring to prevent flour burning on pan bottom.
Add broth and Worcestershire sauce, stirring to prevent lumping.
Bring to boil; season to taste.
Simmer a while.

title: lasagna(italian)
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain.
Add garlic salt, parsley flakes, salt, pepper, tomato paste and water and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna as directed on package.
Mix together eggs and cottage cheese.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan spread about 1/2 cup sauce then alternate layers of lasagna, sauce and egg mixture and Mozzarella until pan is filled.
Top with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fluffy strawberry mold
directions: Pour gelatin in an electric blender.
Add boiling water; blend 30 seconds at low speed.
Scrape sides with a rubber spatula. Cover and blend 15 seconds longer.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and blend 40 to 50 seconds at medium speed, until most of the strawberries are pureed.
Pour immediately into a 4-cup mold or glass serving bowl.
Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours, until set. Unmold onto plate before serving or leave in glass bowl.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 8 servings.

title: pork roast and gravy
directions: Season pork roast with seasoned salt and black pepper. Heat oil in Dutch oven. Dredge the roast in flour and brown on all sides in oil. Heat soups and water together in saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Drain fat from pork. Pour soup mixture over pork roast in the Dutch oven. Cover. Place in a 325° to 350° oven. Bake until well done.

title: grandma shirley's never-fail matzoh balls
directions: Separate the eggs.
Beat whites until peaks form.
Beat yolks with fat.
Add water, salt and pepper to yolks and beat again. Fold in whites gently.
Slowly put in matzoh meal, a little at a time.
Refrigerate your mixture 3 to 4 hours.

title: beef slices in onion sauce
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper and brown on both sides in heated shortening in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven.
Add 1/4 cup of the water, cover tightly and simmer gently from 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat is almost tender.
Add remaining water, 1/4 cupful at a time as needed to keep pan from going dry.
Push meat to one side of pan and carefully place onions in the shortening.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer or until meat is tender and onions are transparent and soft.
Carefully transfer meat and onions to a hot platter and cover to keep warm.
Stir combined flour and sugar into drippings, adding more water if desired.
Heat to boiling and pour over meat and onions.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: 9-layer salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite size pieces.
Chop celery and green pepper very fine.
Slice the onion thin.
Do not cook peas; layer all these and then sugar over this.
Sprinkle 2 or more teaspoons grated Cheddar cheese.
Fry the bacon crisp and crumble on top. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
The salad will do its own combining during this time.
Don't stir.
Should any be leftover, it will keep nicely for 2 or 3 days if covered tightly with foil.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll dough. Press lightly into greased 15 x 10 x 1 jelly roll pan, pressing edges together to line bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.

title: pineapple slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth.

title: jelly roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with paper or foil; grease top of lining.
Sift flour once to measure.
Combine baking powder, salt and eggs in top of double boiler over water.
Beat with electric hand mixer on high for 3 minutes.
Add sugar gradually.
Remove from heat; beat 2 more minutes, adding flour and vanilla.
Pour batter on a clean dish towel dusted with confectioners sugar.
Remove paper.
Spread with jelly and roll up.
Wrap with dish towel to cool.

title: six bean bake
directions: Drain the first 3 cans of beans.
Do not drain the last 3 cans. Brown meat and crumble into a large baking dish; add beans and all other ingredients except bacon.
Mix well and place several bacon strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until thickened. Can be used as a vegetable or main dish.

title: onion bread(teacher's favorite)
directions: Soak onion in water 5 minutes. Combine egg, milk and Tabasco. Add to biscuit mix and stir until blended. Stir in onion and water. Pour into 8-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with caraway seeds. Spoon melted butter over all. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast 5 minutes in 1 cup water.
Combine shortening, sugar and salt.
Add 1 cup water and egg; mix until blended.
Add 3 cups flour; stir until smooth and elastic.
Add remaining flour, stirring; knead.
Refrigerate in greased bowl.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash cranberries; drain.
Cut orange into quarters.
Chop cranberries and orange quarters and stir in pecans and sugar.
Add boiling water to gelatin, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Cool. Stir in cranberry-orange-pecan mixture.
Chill until jelled.
Makes 3 cups.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Combine the oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add the flour and salt which have been mixed together.
Add nuts and roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake until set (not brown) and roll in powdered sugar before and after they cool.

title: tuna and noodles
directions: Place a layer of noodles in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread tuna evenly over noodles.
Place another layer of noodles over the tuna. Spread mushroom soup on top.
Pour half and half over the top then pour in milk to cover noodles.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place small amounts of margarine on top. Bake in oven at 375° for about an hour.

title: tuna linguine primavera
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, adding vegetables during last 4 minutes of cooking time. Drain; return to pan. Add remaining ingredients; toss to cool.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites; beat until stiff.
Gradually add sugar.
Add vanilla.
Chop nuts and crumble saltines; fold into whites.
Spread in pan; bake until golden and firm.
Let cool completely, then spread on Cool Whip, then pie filling.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix Master Mix and sugar together.
Blend slightly beaten egg with fork to water.
Stir water/egg mixture into dry ingredients. Drop onto preheated skillet that has been sprayed with Pam. Skillet should be on medium-high.
Yields 8 to 10 pancakes.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces and place in boiling water for 2 minutes, then drain and cool.
Cube onion. Mix equal parts of sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add lemon juice and garlic salt.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: gumbo(for ten)
directions: Brown 6 slices of bacon and remove from pan.
Add flour and brown.
Add celery, onion, okra, tomatoes and 2 quarts boiling water.
Boil and then simmer for 2 hours.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir with wooden spoon until mixture thickens.
Then blend in last of all raw shrimp, bacon and the crab meat.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes.

title: crab shrimp gumbo
directions: Measure broth into 5 quart Dutch oven.	Add tomatoes, parsley, and celery.
Heat butter in skillet; add peppers, onion, garlic, and okra.
Cover and saute without stirring until onion is soft but not browned.
Add mixture to broth.
Add all of the ingredients except seafood and tabasco.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 2-1/2 hours.
Stir in tabasco and seafood and cook an additional 15 minutes.
May be served over hot rice.
Serves 10-12.

title: ham, cheese & broccoli fondue
directions: Make a doughnut from each bread slice by using 2 different sized round cutters. Butter doughnut and hole pieces and set aside. Place the crusts and scraps of bread in the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch casserole. Sprinkle cheese over bread. Add a layer of broccoli, then ham. Arrange doughnuts and holes on top. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over. Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 325° and bake uncovered for about 50 minutes or until set and brown. Remove from oven and allow to set 10 minutes before serving. Let it set in refrigerator before freezing.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Combine cheese and margarine.
Add flour, pepper and salt.
Add Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet or press down with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Cool.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, mustard and mushrooms.
Add bread and stir until softened.
Stir in cheese.
Pour in baking dish and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday wieners
directions: Heat jelly in fondue pot or crock pot and add wieners.
Heat to boil and serve.

title: chicken salad for 50 people
directions: Bake chicken (do not dry out meat) and cut into large cubes. Mix celery, salt, pepper, mayonnaise, juice/vinegar together.
Add chicken cubes and mix well.
Extras that can be added to salad: green onion to taste, pineapple tidbits, diced apples, sliced green grapes, nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: noodle dough
directions: Sift flour and salt onto a pastry board.
Make a well in the center and add eggs and water.
Work the flour into the egg mixture, adding more water, if necessary, to make a stiff but workable dough. Knead on board until smooth.
Divide dough in half and let it rest for 30 minutes, covered.
Roll out as thin as possible and cut into desired shapes.
Spread noodles on the board and let them dry well before using.
Freezes well.

title: lemon-garlic pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water to desired doneness; drain. Mince garlic.
In pan, heat oil and butter.
Add garlic.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add to other ingredients.
Toss well.
Test for seasoning.
Add pepper and salt for taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: *One-half nuts and 1/2 cup flakes are nice for special occasions.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Whip Pet milk until stiff.
Add sugar.
Beat until sugar is dissolved. Add Kool-Aid and mix well.
Mixture will congeal quickly.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate.
Great summertime dessert.
No cooking.

title: holiday broccoli soup
directions: Saute
onion
in
butter
until tender, but not browned. Add vegetables with
sauce,
chicken
broth, cream and pepper. Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated, about 5 minutes. Makes 5 1/2 cups or 6 servings.

title: congealed salad
directions: Cook fruit and jello until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Add 2 packages of Dream Whip, prepared according to directions on package.
Add cream cheese, softened.
Mix and put in a mold. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute zucchini and chopped onion in oil.
Whip cottage cheese with basil and oregano in blender.
Place alternating layers of squash, cottage cheese and tomato in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: 3 way pool room chili
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook kidney or chili beans on side.
Cook spaghetti on side.
Serve in layers:
bottom spaghetti, second beans with sauce on top.
Serve with oyster crackers.
Serves 4.

title: corn bake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Top with cheese; melt.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Empty milk into large bowl and stir in lemon juice.
Add fruits and Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Pour in crust and refrigerate.

title: great grandma's green tomato sweet relish
directions: Grind vegetables coarsely together.
Put in colander and drain.
Put in a bowl and add canning salt.
Let stand 1/2 hour. Drain again; put in kettle.
Add 1/2 pint (8 ounces) of water and 1/2 pint white vinegar.
Cook 8 minutes.
Stir so it won't scorch. Drain again; put back in kettle.
Add 1 pint white vinegar and 1 pint of water.
Bring to boil, then add turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed.
Stir well.
Cook about 5 minutes and stir.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in layer cake pans.

title: busy housewife slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onions, pepper and pimentos. Make a syrup from vinegar, mustard seed, turmeric, sugar, celery seed and salt. Stir and simmer syrup for 6 minutes. Cool and then pour over slaw mixture. Let set at least 24 hours before using. The longer it sets, the better it is. Will keep as long as 5 or 6 months. Store in glass jar or similar container.

title: oat crackers(wheat free)
directions: Place oats in a bowl.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Add liquid to 4 cups oat flour.
Mix together and knead slightly, adding more flour or water as needed.
Roll out into long roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Slice into 1/2-inch pieces.
Roll out between 2 pieces of plastic or press flat with a tortilla press.
Place on a lightly Pammed baking sheet.
Makes 4 dozen 3-inch crackers.
Or you may roll entire dough directly on cookie sheet and cut in the desired size.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
Burns easily.

title: opal's chocolate pecan cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon. Set aside. Put cocoa, water, cooking oil and butter in a saucepan. Cook until it comes to a boil or it melts. Then mix the first 4 ingredients and the 2nd four ingredients together, stirring well, then add the eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in oblong 9 x 13 pan.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter until soft and creamy.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is light and fluffy.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and spices together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture, making 3 or 4 additions, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir gently and quickly until batter is well blended.
Do not overmix. Spread in well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Let cake cool for 15 to 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 pkg. of Ritz Crackers, crumbled, and pour 1/2 stick of melted margarine over crackers.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: magic pickles
directions: Pour off pickle juice into a large bowl.
Add sugar and Tabasco and stir to dissolve.
Pour pickle juice back over the sliced pickles.
You will probably have more than enough.

title: burrito pie
directions: Combine Bisquick, water and refried beans.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread browned ground beef, taco sauce and grated cheese on next.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, onions, sour cream, etc.

title: creamy mustard sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Blend well.
Chill.
Serve with crab or vegetables.
For a change, try adding chopped onion or garlic.

title: whipped sweet potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes while they're hot.
Mix with the butter, salt and pepper.
Use a hand mixer to beat until smooth.
Serves 6.

title: mindie's cabbage
directions: Cut core out of whole cabbage.
Put bouillon cube into hole; stuff hole with butter.
Wrap cabbage with foil (very well).
Bake at 350° for 5 hours or until tender.
Can cook on grill, it takes a while.

title: granny hobdy's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Grind cranberries and apples. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and congeal.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Spoon apricot preserves evenly over chicken. Sprinkle onion soup mix evenly over chicken.
Pour Russian dressing evenly over chicken.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove cover and stir sauce gently last 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift all
dry ingredients; cut in shortening until like coarse cornmeal.
Combine orange juice and egg.
Pour over dry ingredients all at
once
and mix just enough to dampen.
Fold in coarsely
chopped
nuts, cranberries and orange peel.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for (1) one hour.

title: chesapeake imperial crab
directions: Thoroughly combine mayonnaise, egg, green pepper, pimento, dry mustard, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Add crab meat; stir carefully into mixture.
Divide mixture between 4 cleaned crab shells or individual casseroles, heaping mixture lightly.
Top with thin coating of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot or chilled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth. Saute onion and pepper in margarine until tender.
Mix all ingredients together including 1 to 1 1/2 cups chicken broth.
Put in large baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: ice cream squares
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add coconut and almonds.
Brown.
Add brown sugar, stirring until melted.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of the mixture.
Spread with ice cream.
Top with remaining mixture; freeze.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, mix in refried beans and taco seasoning.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix together picante sauce and sour cream.
Spread over meat mixture. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Serve with corn chips.

title: yogurt pancakes
directions: Whisk together eggs, yogurt, milk and melted butter.
Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Mix wet ingredients and dry until just mixed.
Fold in any kind of fruit (example:
microwave blueberries 30 seconds to 1 minute to thaw, strawberries also go well).

title: steak-n-gravy
directions: Salt and pepper steak to taste.
Place in crock-pot; add cream of mushroom soup and water.
Let cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel onions and thinly slice.
Put butter in 4-quart saucepan and heat until melted.
Add onions and black pepper.
Saute until tender and golden brown.
Sprinkle with flour and stir until flour disappears.
Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Gradually add beef broth, stirring constantly.
Stir in water and bay leaf.
Return to heat and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low and cook soup, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Mix and pour into Bundt cake pan.
Allow Jell-O to set.

title: egg drop soup with peas
directions: Add chopped pork and peas to chicken broth.
Bring to a boil. Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Pour in eggs slowly while stirring the soup.
As soon as the last bit of eggs are in, shut off heat.
Serve with chopped scallions on top.
Serves 4.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: In skillet, brown and crumble sausage; drain and set aside.
In large bowl, beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and sausage.
Pour into greased 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven 40 minutes or until center is done.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mixture into yolks; immediately return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Pour into cooled baked pastry shell.
Spread margarine on pie; sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Add flour, soda and baking powder until well blended.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts like pie crust and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: sugarless fruitcake
directions: Cream margarine with sweetener.
Add eggs one at a time beating well.

Mix dry ingredients reserving 1/2 cup flour. Mix chopped nuts and fruits and add the 1/2 cup flour to them. Mix all ingredients together in a large container. Turn out into a ten inch tube pan or two loaf pans. Bake at 250 degrees for two hours and fifteen minutes for tube pans or two hours for loaves. Let set until cool before removing from pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs on high speed of mixer.
Add sifted flour alternating with milk.
Add baking powder near end of mixing.
Add vanilla and other flavoring at end on slow speed of mixer.
Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: brownies
directions: Melt the chocolate and margarine in a pan.
Beat eggs.
Fold the sugar and melted chocolate mixture into the beaten eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain.
Carefully separate leaves from stem end.
In a large bowl, mix hamburger, sausage, rice, sauerkraut, onion, egg, salt and pepper; mix well.

title: hot pickles
directions: Drain liquid from pickles.
Add all other ingredients and heat to boiling.
Remove garlic buds.
Pack drained pickles into sterilized jars.
Pour hot liquid over pickles and seal.

title: watermelon spice pie
directions: Cut green outer rind and most pulp from watermelon rind; cut into 1/4-inch cubes.
Combine 1 1/2 cups cubes with water to cover in saucepan.
Simmer until tender.
Drain; add sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt, flour, vinegar and raisins; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell in 8-inch pie pan.
Top with remaining pastry; seal edges and cut vents.
Bake at 450° until browned.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake until filling is set.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding and milk; add Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers in pan.
Spread over graham crackers one-half of pudding mixture. Layer another layer of graham crackers, then spread the rest of pudding.
Layer another layer of graham crackers.
Spread melted frosting over the top.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs, water and shortening; dough will be stiff.
Shape into balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dehaven's forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and salt.
Blend until peaks form.
Add chips and nuts.
Mix. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven at 350°.
Turn off heat and leave in oven over night.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Bake in ungreased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour batter into waffle iron just as you would for making waffles.
Don't let cookies get too brown.
Remove and cool.

title: venison stew(crock-pot)
directions: Flour stew meat and brown.
Set aside next 4 ingredients in crock-pot.
Sprinkle next 4 ingredients over vegetables.
Put meat on top.
Pour vegetable juice cocktail over.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: double chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, margarine, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oats, peanut butter chips and chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 11 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Prepare pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage.
Sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Enjoy!

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on oiled cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cups
directions: Drain pineapple; pile into peach halves.
Top each with 1 teaspoon brown sugar and 1 teaspoon butter.
Put on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Serve with ham, sausage or pork chops.

title: sourdough bread
directions: In glass jar, dissolve yeast and 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in 1 cup warm water, sugar and potato flakes.
Let mixture sit out all day, then refrigerate 2 to 5 days, uncovered, or lightly covered.
Remove from refrigerator after 5 days and feed again with 1 cup warm water, 2/3 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons of potato flakes.
Stir well and keep at room temperature for 10 to 12 hours.
Ready to use.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in two well-greased/floured loaf pans for 55 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pumpkin-filled coffeecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch baking pan with no-stick cooking spray.
Beat 1 cup sugar and 1/3 cup margarine until fluffy.
Add egg whites and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in milk and combined flour, 1 cup oats and baking powder.
Combine 1 cup batter, pumpkin and spice; set aside.
Spread half of remaining batter into pan.
Top with pumpkin mixture; spread other half of batter over pumpkin.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.
Divide the apples between 2 (10 ounce) custard cups.
Sprinkle water over apple slices.
Mix flour, sugar, margarine and cinnamon with a fork until crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
Bake, uncovered, until the topping is light golden brown and apples are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: oven roasted meatballs with spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. In large bowl, with hand, mix bread, zucchini, egg white, cheese, garlic salt and pepper until evenly moistened. Add ground turkey and mix just until evenly combined.

title: dressing(15 pound turkey)
directions: Melt butter in large cooker.
Pour in onions, celery and parsley; cook until tender.
In large bowl, add bread, seasonings and 1/2 giblets.
Add cooked mixture to this.
Add broth to get desired moisture.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots 8 to 10 minutes in small amount of water.
Drain and combine with other ingredients; mix well, cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight before serving.
Serve hot or cold.
Saves 2 to 3 weeks.

title: lasagna
directions: Sauce:
Heat oil in large kettle.
Add onions and garlic. Saute 5 minutes.
Add ground beef.
Saute until browned, breaking up meat.
Stir in remaining tomatoes, paste and spices.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 3 hours, until thick.
Remove bay leaves and skim off grease.
Cool and skim again.
Refrigerate until needed.

title: walnut horse shoe cookies
directions: Roll into hand like ball.
Shape them into horse shoe.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: dried beef gravy
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth and bubbly.
Add milk. Continue stirring until mixture thickens and boils.
Add eggs and beef.
Stir and simmer until hot.
Serve over potato or rice.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, spice, eggs, milk, vanilla extract and melted margarine and place into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Cover with the topping.

title: apple-carrot bake
directions: Combine carrots and 1/2 cup water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain carrots and set aside.

title: ham-chicken delight
directions: Fry country ham.
Brown chicken in ham drippings.
Do not add salt.
When brown, place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place ham on top of chicken. In ham-chicken drippings, heat the soup and pour over meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sparkling fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple, reserving juice.
Set fruit aside.
Add enough water to juice to make 1/2 cup. Set aside. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in juice mixture.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pecans, oranges and pineapple.
Pour into a lightly oiled 4-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken cordon bleu casserole
directions: Dip chicken pieces in egg, then bread crumbs.
Brown in a little oil.
Put chicken in baking dish and add cheese and ham pieces.
Mix together soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Saute artichokes in their oil with onions, parsley and garlic. Cool.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add salt and pepper.
Add crackers and cheese.
Add artichokes mixture; bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Set 10 minutes before cutting (7 x 10-inch).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
For use as is on pork.
If used to baste chicken, add 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.

title: texas barbecue
directions: Cook roast in water.
Saute onion, garlic and butter.
Add and cook together all other ingredients.
Add roast that has been cooked and cut fine.
Mix thoroughly.

title: wine cake
directions: Mix all ingredients 5 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into greased, floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cool 5 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Chop fine the lettuce, celery and onion.
Mix with can of peas.
Spread in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar.
Seal over salad.
Sprinkle heavily with cheese and bacon bits.
Refrigerate 12 hours.

title: snitz and knepp
directions: Boil 1/2 hour with ham before adding Knepp.

title: banana split pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 10x sugar and milk, then place in pie shell. On top put bananas and crushed pineapple, then cover with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple- cut in halves.
Mix cream cheese and sugar- add pineapple.
Stir in Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill before serving.

title: gazpacho
directions: In a large bowl, pour undiluted tomato soup.
In small saucepan, heat 2 cans of water to boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in bouillon until dissolved.
Gradually add broth to tomato soup, stirring until blended.
Stir in vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours until well chilled.

title: hot pecan spread
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream with green pepper, onion, beef, garlic, onion salt and pepper.
Put into small casserole. (Can be made ahead.)
Toast pecans in melted butter in small skillet for about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture.
At serving time, bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until hot. Serve with Melba toast rounds or crackers.
Can also be served cold.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until crumbly.
Press into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together the eggs, creamed corn, 1 cup bread crumbs, evaporated milk and salt.
Put in a 3-quart buttered casserole. Top with 1/4 cup bread crumbs and 1/2 stick butter, sliced and placed on top of crumbs.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Good served with meat dishes (ham, turkey, etc.).
Serves 10.

title: buttermilk banana bread
directions: *Add 1 tablespoon vinegar to milk to make buttermilk.

title: turkey hash
directions: Cook and stir celery, onion and green pepper in butter in heavy skillet over medium heat until tender.
Stir in potatoes, turkey and seasonings.
Cook over low heat, about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add gravy; cook and stir until mixture is hot.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
In a 1-quart microwave safe casserole, combine potato slices and water.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 5 to 7 minutes or until tender, stirring after every 3 minutes.
Drain potato slices well.
Dollop cheese spread onto the potato slices. Cook, uncovered, on High for 30 to 60 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Gently stir the melted cheese into the potato slices. Serves 2.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, milk and extract.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Roll on floured surface to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Cool, then decorate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Beat 3 eggs well;
add 1 1/4 cups
oil
and
cups
sugar.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour, 2 medium apples
(peeled,
cored
and
chopped), 1 cup shredded coconut and 1
cup chopped walnuts or pecans.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into
tube
pan
and bake 1 hour (more or less). Remove from
pan after
cooled
about 30 minutes and top with following while still warm.

title: watergate
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, oleo and pecans.
Press in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly browned.
Let cool.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix; then press like a pie crust into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until light brown, about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt butter, dump all ingredients together.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian pie(makes two 8-inch pies)
directions: Bake pie shells at 350° until brown.
Cool.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix all.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and coconut.
Chill.

title: cabana cafe's white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Wash chicken and cover with 1/2 spice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onions until translucent.
Add chiles, garlic and spices and saute 1 minute.
Drain beans and add beans and stock to pot.
Add onions, spice mixture and beer.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Dice chicken into quarter-sized pieces.
Add to stock. Simmer.
Remove from heat.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: creamy jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O until dissolved.
Let cool.
Take out of refrigerator and add the buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Fold in until lumps disappear.
Then add the nuts.
Pour in an 8-inch square dish. Cool at least 4 hours.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter or margarine until tender. Mix with chicken and mushroom soups, cheese, broccoli and one cup rice.
Grease a large casserole dish.
Put mixture in dish.
Top with remaining rice.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: date nut balls
directions: Take teaspoonful and roll into balls, then roll in coconut, 1/2 cup should be enough for entire batch.
Cool.
Can also be frozen.

title: italian bars
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; remove from heat and cool. Combine eggs, sugars and beat with wooden spoon. When dissolved, add baking soda, cinnamon and stir, then add melted butter. Lastly, add flour 1 cup at a time. Arrange into baking sheet, making 3 rows. Smooth top with little water and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove and pour icing. Cut when cooled. Makes 3 logs.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in greased casserole dish.
Top with Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Wash potatoes well.
Depending on your preference, peel or leave skin on.
Thinly slice about 4 cups.
I use my grater (it goes fast).
Heat butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook onion in butter, about 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly; remove from heat.
Stir in milk and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Spread potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese sauce over potatoes.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Mix remaining cheese and the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over potatoes; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until top is brown and bubbly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press crescent rolls into a pan.
Cook sausage and drain. Sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle hash browns over sausage, then top with Cheddar cheese.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and bake for 30 minutes in an 350° oven.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Crock-pot will make 3 layers, depending on size of the crock-pot.
Boil the chicken.
Then debone it.

title: never last cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl and let set for 2 minutes. Use spoon only and mix well, but do not beat.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: quick rolls
directions: Shape basic dough/roll recipe into small balls.
Brush with melted butter.
Arrange 4 balls in greased muffin tin cup.
Bake according to directions on recipe.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until done, at least 30 minutes.
Let cool; debone and skin.
Place back in broth.
Put soup in.
Bring to boil; pour in rice.
Simmer until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli casserole(low-fat)
directions: Cook noodles and broccoli as directed and drain.
In double boiler, mix yogurt, flour and mustard.
Heat. Add milk
slowly. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted.
Layer noodles, broccoli and turkey in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over all and bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in an 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thick. Cool.
Stir in 1 pint fresh strawberries. Put in baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk in large bowl; add whipped topping and mix until smooth.
Line 8 x 11 1/2-inch pan or dish with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over crackers.
Cover with a layer of crackers and pour the other half of mixture.
Add another layer of crackers.
Top with frosting, beginning at edges and spread to center.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Garnish with cherries. Keep refrigerated.

title: jill's crab meat dip(the special occasion dip)
directions: Microwave cream cheese to soften; spread evenly in serving dish (about 1/2-inch deep).
Evenly place crab meat over cheese and then cover with cocktail sauce.
Best with Ritz or club crackers.

title: mom's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pie crusts.
Makes 2.
Bake at 325° until center is firm.
(May need to reduce heat during baking, depending on your oven.)

title: banana nut chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water and set aside.
In saucepan, mix 1/2 c. sugar, salt
and milk.
Cook over low heat stirring until scalded and remove from heat.
Take half the cooked mixture, stir with egg yolks and return to saucepan.
Cook over low heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
Cool over bowl of ice.
When mixture is partially set, beat with mixer until smooth.
Blend in vanilla.
Gently fold thawed Cool Whip into mixture.
Make meringue with egg whites, cream of tartar and sugar.
Gently add to cooked mixture.
Add bananas, nuts and cherries.
Pile into pie shells and chill about 2 hours.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix sugar and oleo together with egg, milk and vanilla.
Put dough in refrigerator for 2 hours or more to chill. Roll out the dough on wax paper sprinkled with flour.
Cut dough with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine and sugar.
Cool.
Add beaten egg, baking powder, salt and baking soda into flour.
Stir in nuts and chocolate bits.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into about 24 small squares.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and continue to beat until mixed well. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour in canister of ice crem freezer.
Add milk to fill line if necessary.
Start freezer.

title: jam kolaches
directions: Cream together margarine and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add flour; mix well.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured surface.
Cut with 2-inch round cutter.
Place on lightly greased (Pam) cookie sheet with sides touching.
Combine jam and walnuts (nuts keep jam from spreading out too much); drop 1 to 2 teaspoons on dough rounds.
Fold opposite sides together and pinch with thumb and forefinger, once each.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.
Dust with powdered sugar while warm.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Measure flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda into sifter.
Cream butter with sugar until well blended in a large bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift in flour mixture; adding alternately with sour cream and blending well to make thick batter.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 4 inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Spread into 2 inch rounds and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 12 minutes or until lightly golden around edges.

title: strawberry snow
directions: Mix jello, water and sugar.
Mash strawberries; mix in and chill for 1 1/2 hours.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Crumble cake; put into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture over top.
Chill.

title: pork and soy sauce with onions
directions: Thinly slice the pork and onions.
Heat the oil in pan and fry the pork.
Add the onions; continue cooking over medium heat until tender.
Add the sugar, salt, soy sauce, soup stock, sherry and m.s.g.; boil for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add pepper to taste.
Mix the cornstarch in the cold water; add to the soup to thicken.
Add the green peas and serve, piping hot.

title: italian sausage
directions: Cook sausage until almost done, and add the onion and green peppers.
Cook to desired tenderness.
This makes enough for two people.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir well.
Put
in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hollywood squares
directions: Combine margarine, graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and peanut butter; mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate dipped fruit
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring constantly until smooth. Spear fruit with toothpicks; dip into chocolate. Place on waxed paper or stick toothpicks into a block or styrofoam to harden.

title: libby's bean dip
directions: Put in glass casserole dish and bake at 350° until cheese and cream cheese melts.
Mix thoroughly.
Magnificent on tortilla chips.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in pie crust.
Heat sugar, cornstarch, Jell-O, food coloring and water over medium heat until thick.
Pour over strawberries.
Chill 2 hours, then top with Cool Whip.

title: san francisco clam dip
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until transparent.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until creamy and heated through.
Serve warm with assorted crackers or chips.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Halve avocado; with spoon, remove pulp and mash. Mix in all of the ingredients except for the corn tortillas. Use them to dip.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup of the cookies into pudding mixture.
Spoon into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Garnish with gummy worms if desired.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions; drain.
Add margarine to hot spaghetti, stir in eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Form into a crust in greased 10-inch pie pan.
Spread with cottage cheese.
In skillet, cook sausage until brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and heat through.
Turn meat mixture into spaghetti crust. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and bake until melted, 5 minutes.

title: lemon batter fish
directions: In
a
medium
bowl,
mix
flour,
water, 1/3 cup lemon juice, egg,
baking powder, salt and sugar. Dip fish in lemon juice. Coat
with	flour,	then dip in batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown. Drain on towels. Serve hot.

title: party punch
directions: Mix juices; add club soda.
Float ice ring.
Serves 32.

title: corn pudding
directions: Process 1 can of corn, flour and next 6 ingredients in a blender or food processor until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides. Transfer to a bowl. Stir in remaining 3 cans of corn. Pour mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set. Makes 12 servings.

title: banana coffee shake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until smooth in blender.
Pour into wine glasses or goblets.
Garnish each serving with shaved chocolate.
Makes 2 servings.

title: macaroni salad for two
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring lightly; cover and chill several hours before serving.

title: moe's chicken and dumpling stew
directions: Melt butter in a large pan or Dutch oven.
Put your chicken and coat.
Add your onions, garlic, 1/3 cup Saucerie, salt and pepper to taste.
Add some water or milk and stir.
Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add your carrots, potatoes and more of the Saucerie up to 1/3 cup more, go by taste.
Cook until the carrots and the potatoes are done.
If you need to add more liquid (milk or water) do so for a good consistency.
About 10 minutes before stew is done, take biscuits out of can and put on top of stew.
Cook with the lid on for about 5 to 7 minutes.
Take lid off and cook for another 5 to 7 minutes.
Feeds 4 to 6 people.

title: austin's pasta
directions: Cook pasta. Drain. Mix dressing as instructed on the back of the package. Drain mushrooms and olives. Mix all ingredients together. Chill.

title: cool and creamy pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine pumpkin, 1/2 carton whipped topping, pudding mix and spice.
Beat at low speed until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Spread into crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Quick chill in freezer, 10 to 15 minutes, until ready to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: play dough
directions: Put water and salt in kettle; stir and heat to 80° or until bubbles on bottom.
Remove from heat and add oil, alum and food coloring.
Add flour quickly; stir to prevent lumps and knead. Will keep soft in plastic airtight container or will harden if left out to dry.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine and add graham cracker crumbs, powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and frost over the top.
When chocolate is set, cut into small squares.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Combine water, yeast and sugar.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Add salt, margarine, egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat smooth.
Work in remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 24 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine
softened
cream cheese and Cheddar cheese. Add pimento, onion,
sauce and salt.
Mix well. Shape into ball or log. Chill	several
hours.
Roll in pecans or parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: crayfish etouffee
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients until veggies are soft, then add crawfish and saute a little.
Add soup and water.
Simmer awhile.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put chops in a baking dish.
Put rice over them.
Add onion and pepper; pour in boiling water and tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Blend in condensed milk; slowly add lime juice and mix well.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites; beat until foamy.
Continue to beat and add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time until forms peaks.
Fold 7 tablespoons of meringue into filling.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and top with remaining meringue.
Bake at 330° until brown.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemonade.
Mash bananas; blend in blender.
Freeze.
Add chilled Sprite to partially thawed punch.
Serves 50.

title: applesauce(makes 3 cups)
directions: Put apples and water into saucepan. Turn heat to medium and cook, stirring often, until the apples become tender, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Add sugar and lemon juice. Stir to blend.
Cook another 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and mash with fork.

title: sweet and creamy pumpkin dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add pumpkin and remaining ingredients. Blend. Chill 30 minutes. Serve with gingersnaps, apples, sweet breads.

title: connie's crazy chocolate cake
directions: Put the ingredients in a mixing bowl in the order given.
Do not stir until the water is added.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Bake on 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes until done.
Cake is done when a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: kelly's cheese soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and noodles until done.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add frozen carrots to potato mixture.
Add Velveeta and soups.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add mushrooms. Cook in crock-pot up to 6 hours.

title: steamed asparagus with tomato-basil dip
directions: Whisk together first 5 ingredients until blended. May chill up to 2 days, if desired.
Snap off tough ends of asparagus; remove scales with vegetable peeler, if desired. Cook in boiling water to cover 3 minutes until crisp tender.
Plunge asparagus into ice water to stop the cooking process.
Drain. Cover and chill until ready to serve with dip.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix until crumbly, press into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: buffalo chips cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine melted oleo and Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine and add to mixture flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Now, stir in oatmeal, Rice Krispies, chocolate chips, coconut and nuts. Drop by 1/4 cup on large cookie sheet (6 to a sheet).
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oleo until creamy. Alternate flour and eggs. Add vanilla. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch bread pudding
directions: Cook sugar and butter together until brown.
Heat 2 cups of milk and add to sugar.
Remove from heat; let stand for about 5 minutes.
Soak bread in remaining 1/2 cup of milk in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Beat the 2 eggs; mix with the sugar mixture.
Mix in the vanilla and pour over the bread.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with whipped cream.

title: dinner in foil
directions: Starting with a patty, place 4 ingredients on a large sheet of foil.
Season to taste.
Wrap and seal.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nut bread
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 1 hour in the oven at 350°.
