title: impossible cheese cake
directions: Blend milk, eggs, sugar and baking mix in blender on high for 15 seconds.
Add softened cream cheese and blend on high for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into greased 9 x 11-inch pie plate.
Serve with fruit topping or Sour Cream Topping.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil to 350°.
Mix milk and egg. Put breasts in milk and egg mixture, then dredge in bread crumbs. Brown lightly in oil.
Place breasts in baking dish and sprinkle remaining bread crumbs over top.
Pour lemon juice and wine over crumbs, making sure the crumbs are wet.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, then reduce temperature to 325° and cook another 20 minutes.
Serve with noodle roni with herb sauce.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Add coconut, raisins, nuts and vinegar; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: rice krispies candy
directions: Heat sugar and Karo syrup until sugar melts. Add peanut butter to sugar and Karo. In large bowl, add mixture to the 6 cups of Rice Krispies and mix well. Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour Rice Krispie mixture into pan and press evenly.

title: pork cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 350 degree oven for 10 to 15 minutes; reduce to 325 degrees and cook until tooth pick comes out clean when inserted in the middle of the cake.

title: hubbard squash
directions: Cut the squash into fairly large pieces.
Boil in salted water 15 minutes. Drain. Sprinkle with pepper.
Make a sauce by combining the remaining ingredients.
Pour over hot, drained squash and toss gently. Serve immediately.

title: broccoli-rice-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in margarine and then add soup and 1 can water.
Add broccoli, Cheez Whiz and cooked rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in casserole, sprinkle with paprika and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
This will serve 12.

title: pink panther poop
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk, pie filling, Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans in large bowl.
Chill in refrigerator for one hour.
Sprinkle with coconut and miniature marshmallows before serving if desired.
Serves 12.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Add chopped onion and chopped cucumber.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons dried parsley flakes over the noodles.
Marinate for 2 days.
Add 1 chopped tomato and chopped green pepper.
Will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and toss with stuffing mix.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Add 1/2 stuffing mix and pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.

title: strawberry loaf bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and oil, berries and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Layer the following ingredients on a large serving place:

title: caramel dip with fruit
directions: Melt caramels and milk in a microwavable dish in microwave. Cool slightly.
Stir in pudding.
Soak apple wedges in pineapple juice to prevent browning.
Serve apples and dip together.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Combine apples, sugar and cranberries in a 2-quart casserole. Top with rest of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until light brown and bubbly.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, water and seasoning.
Cook slow. Mix milk and cheese.
Melt and set aside. Cook lasagna in saltwater.
Layer in 9 x 13 pan 3 lasagna, hamburger mixture, then cheese.
Repeat these layers until there are three layers of each.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook celery and onion in hot oil until tender-crisp.
Combine soup and milk; mix with all remaining ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: spicy carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven for 10 minutes at 350°.
Combine dry ingredients and mix well.
Add eggs and oil and mix.
Now add carrots and beat on medium speed with electric mixer about 2 minutes.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) cake pans.
Pour cake batter into pans and bake 25-30 minutes.

title: yellow cake(scratch cake; i use for coconut cake)
directions: Mix as you usually do, when making cakes.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Use your favorite 7 minute frosting or the White Mountain Frosting from Betty Crocker cookbook.
Eat and enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove bones and tear chicken into small pieces.
Mix with both soups.
Add salt.
Pour into 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble crackers and add to melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Bake in 350° oven about 1 hour or until crackers are brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until almost tender and drain.
Put in casserole dish and add mushroom soup and mayonnaise, cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix all together.
Put more cheese and cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peach jam
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in 5-quart casserole dish. Microwave, uncovered, at High for 5 minutes.
Stir well. Microwave, uncovered, at High for 15 to 17 minutes, or until mixture reaches a full, rolling boil.
Stir in pectin.
Skim off foam with spoon.
Pour into hot jelly jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature until cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill at least 2 hours or longer so flavors can blend.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Combine candies, flour, apples, topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into frozen regular 9-inch pie crust and sprinkle with 1/2 cup pecan pieces.
Bake at 375° on preheated baking sheet for 40 to 45 minutes.
Store at room temperature.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all ingredients and simmer 15-20 minutes.
Then add cream cheese with the meat mixture to a crock pot.
Stir well on low heat.
Serve with corn or tortilla chips.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup; bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter; blend well.
Pour over Rice Krispies, mixing well.
Press into a buttered cake pan.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips.
Smooth over top.

title: buccellato(easter bread)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Prepare yeast according to package instructions.
Add to egg mixture. Add flour, a little at a time, until soft dough is formed.
Put into greased large bowl or kettle.
Let rise until double in size.
Shape into desired forms.
Let rise again until double in size. Bake at 300° to 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Be sure to grease tin before placing desired form.

title: low-fat pot pies
directions: Brown turkey and onions.
Mix soup, vegetables and turkey together.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place in oven and heat until nice and hot.
Put biscuits on another pan and bake until almost done.
Take soup mixture out of oven and place biscuits on top.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: steak stir-fry on a bed of rice
directions: Cut steak into strips and halve the strips.
Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in 2 tablespoons margarine or cooking oil. Stir constantly.
Never overcook.
When desired doneness is reached, put these ingredients in another container and put your stripped steaks in the container with the cooking oil or margarine. Cook until tender, constantly stirring.
Add tomato sauce and cover for 15 minutes.
Then add your onion, bell pepper and mushrooms. Cover for 5 more minutes.
That's it!
Start the rice to boil and lower heat.
Upon completion, place stir-fry on a bed of rice.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Melt butter, being careful not to get it too brown.
Stir in crackers.
Grease 3-quart casserole, 9 x 13-inch size.
Put vegetables in; add cubed cheese on top and then put cracker mixture on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Add egg, salt, soda and flour.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Debone chicken.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Pour chicken soup over chicken.
Mix other ingredients; pour over chicken.
Pour broth over above mixture.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: dark chocolate frosting
directions: In double boiler combine sweetened condensed milk, chocolate and salt.
Cook until chocolate melts and mixture is very thick. Add water and vanilla and stir rapidly until smooth.
Cool 10 minutes.
Use to frost one 8-inch or 9-inch two layer cake or one 13 x 9-inch cake or 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Rub chicken in oil and brown in skillet.
While browning chicken, sweat the vegetables in Dutch oven casserole.
In casserole, make a bottom layer of carrot, celery, onion and garlics.
Over first layer, lay the chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper, then with parsley.
Make one more layer of the vegetables, ending with chicken.
Add cognac, warmed, and flambe carefully.
Season the top layer and add the wine.
Place a double layer of foil over the casserole and then add the lid.
Heat briefly on top of stove burner, then place in the preheated oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Serve chicken directly from the casserole.
A delicious sauce is self made, the garlics cook down to a soft and wonderful nutty flavor.
Serve with plenty of crusty French bread, wine, fresh fruits for dessert.

title: baked chicken liver and onions
directions: In a flat casserole dish, slice onions very thin to cover bottom.
Place livers in a single layer over onions.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Slice another layer of onions on top.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons soy sauce over this.
Dot with 1 to 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until livers are firm.

title: date bars
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Blend all ingredients well.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat together until creamy.
Pour into buttered Pyrex baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This makes its own crust!
Take from oven; cool for 10 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Add corn.
Beat egg whites; add to corn.
Bake (in water) 1/2 hour at 350° for until it puffs up.

title: peter paul mound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Make 4 layers in pans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Use wax paper in bottom of pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Stir in crushed pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: wassail
directions: Put all in percolator and let perk.
Makes about 8 to 10 cups.

title: taco hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco mix and water.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Put into pie shell.
Add chopped onion and green pepper on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with egg and milk mixture.
Bake at 350° for 4 minutes.

title: crispy oven chicken
directions: Crush corn flakes until very fine.
Stir in salt and pepper. Dip chicken pieces in milk, then corn flake crumbs.
Place on lightly greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: chinese chicken
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil until hot.
Place water chestnuts, celery, carrots and cabbage in skillet.
Cover; cook over medium-high heat for about 2 minutes.
Add baked chicken. Pour chicken broth in center of mixture.
Cover and steam 1 minute.
Dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add soy sauce; toss with chicken-vegetable mixture to thicken sauce to cover all ingredients.
Serve immediately over rice, noodles or chow mein noodles.

title: sweet chicken
directions: Mix dressing, preserves and onion soup.
Cover chicken. Marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes uncovered, then 30 minutes more covered.

title: layered hamburger pie
directions: Mix beef with egg, crumbs, salt, herbs, mustard, cumin and garlic powder.
Pat evenly into a 9-inch pie pan to make a crust.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Best if made the day before.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix together and spread (as best you can) into a large oblong cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes or until browned at 350°.
Let cool.

title: asparagus with mushrooms
directions: Cook asparagus as directed on can.
Drain in small saucepan. Combine margarine, mushrooms, almonds, basil and pepper.
Beat well.
Heat thoroughly.
Place asparagus on serving platter; pour mushroom mixture over spears.
Serve at once.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, squeeze out and chop.
Add sour cream and mayonnaise.
Finely chop water chestnuts and green onions or onion; add vegetable soup mix.
Add this mixture to the spinach, sour cream and mayonnaise mixture.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: First get milk. Then put in sugar.
Then put in cinnamon. Then you need to put in sprinkles.
Then put in vanilla.
Then stir it. Then let it sit for a while, about 1 minute.
Then put it in the freezer for 1 hour and a half.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt morsels with condensed milk. Remove from heat.
Stir in other ingredients.
Spread evenly onto waxed paper lined 8-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Store at room temperature.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt oleo; add mustard and Durkee sauce.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients and heat slowly until heated.
This will scorch if heated too fast.
Delicious on barbecued chicken.

title: face paint
directions: In each cup of the muffin tin mix 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1/2 teaspoon water, 1/2 teaspoon cold cream and a couple drops of food coloring, a different color for each cup.
Stir.
You're ready to go use the paint.

title: pecan cocoons
directions: Beat butter or margarine until lemon colored.
Then add other ingredients gradually.
Roll into cocoon shapes and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
While they are still hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: seafood treat
directions: Cut off crusts from bread slices; roll them thin.
Melt butter and cheese over low.
Add meat and onion juice; spread on bread slice and roll like a jelly roll.
Freeze rolls on a tray, then seal in freezer bag.
When ready to serve, cut little frozen roll in 1/2; dip in melted butter.
Place on jelly roll pan and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: eggnog christmas salad
directions: Soften unflavored gelatin in the undrained pineapple and the lime juice for 5 minutes.
Cook and stir over medium heat until gelatin dissolves.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in eggnog. Chill until partially set.
Fold in celery.
Turn into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until almost firm.
Heat cranberry juice to boiling; stir in raspberry gelatin until dissolved.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in cranberry relish.
Pour over eggnog layer and chill until set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, onion, 1/4 cup cracker crumbs, egg, sugar, salt and pepper.
Add squash; mix well.
Pour into lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining cracker crumbs over squash mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: continental punch
directions: In quart punch bowl or large glass salad bowl, combine fruit juices and sugar.
Pour over ice and stir in gingerale.
Serve with an ice cube or crushed ice in each glass.

title: hocus pocus cake(makes 8 servings)
directions: In small bowl, mix cookie crumbs, sugar, flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg yolks until thick, about 5 minutes.
At medium speed, gradually blend in flour mixture alternately with water, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Fold into batter.
Spread batter into foil lined and greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: mimaw's cool rice salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, bring peas, salt and water to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in instant rice and onion.
Cover and let stand 13 minutes.
Cool.
Stir in mayonnaise and pickles.
Chill.

title: custard
directions: Scald milk. Beat egg yolks. Add sugar and salt. Stir constantly when adding to the hot milk. Return to double boiler. Stir until thick. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into custard. Serve cold.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Place bread into bowl; mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into bread pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: reese's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Cream together the margarine, eggs (added one at a time) and milk.
Add to the first mixture.
Add the mixture of fruits and nuts.
Pour apricot brandy over fruit mixture.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 275° for 15 minutes.
Makes 20 dozen.

title: low calorie muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Add water to egg whites.
Add sugar and cream of tartar; beat until stiff.
Add orange peel and flavoring.
Quickly fill greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 16 muffins.
One muffin equals 39 calories or 1/2 bread exchange.

title: better than robert redford cake
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Put in baked crust.
Prepare pudding according to box directions and layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add remainder of Cool Whip and cool.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients with 1/2 cup of milk, mix with a mixer.
Add to rest of milk and bring to a boil slowly.
I use a hand mixer to make pudding creamier.

title: grandmother's old-fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter gradually; add sugar.
Then add eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamy mixture. Place 1 tablespoonful of mixture per a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: tally ho salad dressing
directions: Put ingredients in a jar, and shake well.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: skinny cake
directions: Mix cake mix with diet Coke. Bake according to directions on cake mix.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Add boiling water to jello and sugar; stir until dissolved. Add strawberries; stir until thawed.
Place in refrigerator until syrupy, then stir in whipped cream.
Place 1/2 the pieces of angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then pour 1/2 the strawberry mixture over cake.
Repeat layers.
Let set until firm; cut into squares to serve.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Place chickens in a deep kettle.
Add water, sherry, salt, curry powder, onion and celery.
Bring to a boil and cover tightly.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour.
Remove from heat and strain broth.
Refrigerate chicken and broth at once.
When chicken is cool enough to handle, remove meat, discard skin and bones; cut into bite size pieces.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Remove fat from chicken broth and measure broth.
Follow package directions for cooking rice, including seasoning packet, using chicken broth as the liquid.
Add water if there is not enough broth.
Mix sour cream with undiluted mushroom soup, then add chicken, cooked rice and mushrooms.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Heat margarine and broth together until margarine is melted.
Pour half of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour the chicken mixture over mix and spread evenly.
Pour broth and butter over top of this.
Beat together the milk and eggs and add.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Spread mushroom soup on top.
Add rest of stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix in bowl sugar, flour and soda.
In a saucepan put oleo, shortening and cocoa.
Add 1 cup water and boil.
Pour this mixture over the flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir and put in a sheet cake pan.
Be sure to grease and flour the pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with Texas Sheet Cake Topping.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool.
Grate into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.

title: five day pickles
directions: First Day:
Dissolve salt in half gallon boiling water.
Pour over cucumbers.
If this does not fill jar, finish filling with boiling water.
Drain after 24 hours.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Cook each item separately until tender; mix all items together. Salt to taste. Add a little Worcestershire sauce to taste. Simmer until ready to eat.

title: feed the crowd casserole
directions: Brown meat; add onions and pimento and cook at medium temperature for 10 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole and add 3 cups of cooked noodles.
Mix cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soup plus 8 ounces sour cream and corn together.
Pour on top of meat and noodles into casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: fried chicken with walnuts
directions: Toast walnuts at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut chicken in 1/2-inch cubes and mix with egg white and 1 tablespoon cornstarch and ginger.
Stir-fry in hot oil in wok or skillet for 3 minutes until chicken changes color.
Add wine and soy sauce.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes, then add cornstarch and water mixture and walnuts.
Mix well and stir to heat through.
Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: cass' wedding day punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Cool.
Combine next 4 ingredients with sugar mixture.
Pour into a 5-quart freezer container and freeze until firm.
Remove mixture from freezer several hours before serving (mixture should be slushy).
Pour into punch bowl and stir in ginger ale.
Yields 2 1/2 gallons.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine melted margarine with salt and pepper in shallow bowl.
Place bread crumbs in shallow dish. Unfold chicken and dip one piece at a time into margarine, then bread crumbs, pressing to coat all sides.
Arrange chicken in single layer on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until brown and fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
When done, chicken will not be pink when sliced through thickest part.

title: donna louise's slaw
directions: Coarsely cut cabbage with knife or chop with dough cutter. Add remaining ingredients.

title: goulash(slop)
directions: Crumble and fry hamburger; drain.
Cook and drain 1 box macaroni.
Combine in frypan with corn, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cook on low for 10 minutes.
Add cheese and continue cooking until cheese melts.

title: mike's new york style taters
directions: Peel and cut in half potatoes; boil for 25 minutes.
Let them cool after cooking.
Chop up onions and microwave for 10 to 12 minutes (keep covered while in microwave).
Cut up potatoes in chunks and let cool.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, onions, sliced mushrooms and Cheez Whiz first.
Then add cooled chunks of potatoes and mix all together.
In a 10-inch Corning Ware bowl, spray with Pam or butter spray.
Put everything into bowl and sprinkle over top with 100% Parmesan cheese.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook for 55 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins about 5 minutes; drain.
Add flour to sugar, then to raisins.
Put in butter.
Stir in egg yolks one at a time.
Add pecans and cook until thick.
Put into an unbaked double crust pie shell.
Bake until brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Rinse in hot water.
Combine noodles with drained tuna, celery and green onions.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.
Spoon half mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with half zucchini.
Repeat layers. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with chopped tomato.

title: sliced apples and dip
directions: Quarter apples with peel; put in salt water and let stand awhile before using.
Mix together brown sugar and cream cheese and use as dip for apples.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
Beat together the wet ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.
(Batter will be thick.)
Mixture may be stored in the refrigerator up to 3 weeks. Bake in muffin tins for 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Yields 40 muffins.

title: connie's broccoli casserole
directions: In a large bowl mix milk, soup and rice; add broccoli and mix. Add cheese.
Saute onion in butter until tender (do not brown). Add onions and butter to mixture.
Put in a large casserole. Crush crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: marinated cucumber and onion slices
directions: Place cucumbers and onions in covered container.
Combine sour cream, vinegar, salt and pepper; pour over slices.
Marinate until ready to serve.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Lightly brown pie crust.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased cake pan.
Blend sugar and cinnamon mix in lemon juice and water; pour over apples.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse beans; set aside.
In large pot or Dutch oven, saute onion and garlic.
Add clean beans, ham, smoked sausage, salt, pepper, cayenne, marjoram and enough water to cover.
Cover and cook until beans are done.
May need to add water from time to time.
To serve, place cooked white rice on plate and add cooked beans; garnish with chopped green onions.

title: chocolate chip-brandy souffle
directions: Measure off a length of aluminum foil long enough to encircle 4-cup souffle dish.
Fold in half lengthwise.
Fasten to dish with tape or string so collar is about 6 inches higher than rim.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in double boiler.
Add vanilla and coloring.
Stir in corn flakes.
Mix until well coated.
Keep warm while dropping by teaspoonfuls on wax paper.
Top each with red hots.
These are great to make with children.

title: spiced peach dumplings
directions: In saucepan, mix peaches, sugar, butter and lemon juice. Bring to boil.
In large bowl, mix all other ingredients, except nuts.
Drop this mixture by spoonfuls into hot peach mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes. Serve hot with light cream or ice cream.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well; store in an airtight container.
Mix 1/3 cup mix and 1 cup hot water.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together the Cool Whip and pudding until green in color. Add marshmallows and drained pineapple.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 8 (4-ounce) servings.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Trim crusts off bread and cut in 4 strips for 24 crisps or cut in half for 48 crisps.
Using 2 forks, roll bread in Eagle Brand, coating all sides.
Then roll in coconut.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once from baking sheet.
Makes 24 to 48 crisps.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: About 1 hour ahead, set out eggs.
Start heating oven to 350°. Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs until very thick and light, about 5 minutes. Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Beat in lemon juice. Fold in flour mixture, small amount at a time.
Add hot milk. Stir quickly until blended.
Immediately turn batter into ungreased pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.
Use 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or tube pan.

title: lime fruit dip
directions: In a small mixing bowl beat the cream cheese until smooth. Beat in marshmallow creme and fold in yogurt and food coloring. Cover and refrigerate until until serving time.

title: teriyaki burgers
directions: Shape ground beef into 4 patties, each about 3/4 inch thick. Mix remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto patties.
Turn patties; let stand 10 minutes.
Grill patties about 4 inches from medium coals, turning once, until desired doneness, 5 to 7 minutes on each side for medium.
Serve on toasted sesame seed buns.

title: crunchy oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
together
in
large bowl, the margarine, sugars, eggs and and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture. Stir in, by hand, the oatmeal and corn flakes.

title: apple pie cake
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.

title: quick buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut 1/2 cup butter into flour with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: lots o brownies
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa; turn out fire and add sugar.
Mix eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add this to cocoa mixture.
Add nuts. Pour into greased and floured (2) 10-inch square cake pans or (1) large grill pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut while warm.

title: chinese beef with peppers
directions: Heat pan.
Add oil and garlic.
Remove garlic when brown.
Add beef; fry a few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soup stock and continue to cook a few seconds.
Add mixture of cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Cook until sauce thickens, stirring slowly.
Add green pepper and fresh chopped ginger.
Heat thoroughly and serve hot with rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: delicious lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large mixing bowl (medium speed) for 10 to 12 minutes.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Pour in batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until a toothpick comes out clean.
When cake is baking, make sauce.

title: new york style cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Spray the sides of a 9-inch springform pan with vegetable cooking spray.

title: nana's spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Put in greased casserole; cover with remaining stuffing mix (3/4 cup). Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant provencal
directions: Peel and cut eggplant.
Peel and cut tomatoes into 6 slices; cut green pepper into 4 rings each.
Combine herbs; set aside. Place 6 eggplant slices in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with 1/4 teaspoon olive oil.
Lightly salt and pepper and 1/4 teaspoon herb mix.
Layer 6 onion rings, 6 tomato slices and 6 green peppers on top.
Repeat oil and seasonings.
Sprinkle each stack of vegetables with 1/4 teaspoon minced garlic.
Repeat seasoned layers with remaining ingredients in a second 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan and Gruyere.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 12 servings.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix everything in bowl the night before serving to insure proper blend of flavor.
Serve with crackers.

title: fig preserve--to jar
directions: Wash and cut off tops of figs.
Cook for at least 2 1/2 hours.
Give 4 quarts.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt and cool shortening; add sugar, eggs and molasses.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients and add slowly.
Chill dough.
Form into small balls.
Roll in sugar and bake on a greased cookie pan for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Use same amount of jelly and mustard.
Mix jelly and mustard in crock-pot.
Add wieners that have been cut in 1/2-inch pieces. Marinate for 2 hours.
Serve hot.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: apple fritters
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and well beaten egg.
Pare and core apples.
Slice about 1/4-inch thick. Dip each piece in batter and fry until golden brown.
Drain on a paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: perfect pumpkin pie
directions: Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 375°.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown stew beef in the oil in a Dutch oven.
Add onions, tomatoes, beef broth, celery and spices.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add carrots and potatoes; cook until they are tender. Before serving, add enough cornstarch to thicken.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; remove skin and bones and cut up. Saute celery and onions until tender.
Mix with stuffing and 1/2 can chicken broth.
Mix the 2 cans of soup together and add rest of broth.
Grease casserole dish and layer stuffing mix, chicken and soup.
Reserve some stuffing for top of layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: peach and blueberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix peaches lightly with 2 tablespoons of sugar, then cornstarch and then the lemon juice.
Roll out the pie dough and press into a 9-inch pie plate, crimping the edges. Arrange peaches around the sides, leaving the center for the blueberries.
Toss the blueberries with the remaining 1 tablespoon sugar.
Pour into the center of the filled pie.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until the pastry is golden and the fruit is soft and bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together; drop into a greased muffin pan. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Chop cucumber and onion and mix with other ingredients. Pour over cooked noodles and refrigerate.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Cream together the eggs, sugar and butter.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 370° for 45 minutes.

title: italian coconut cake
directions: Cream crisco and sugar; add egg yolks and beat well. Combine flour, soda and pinch of salt. Add to creamed mixture. Alternating flour and buttermilk. Add vanilla, coconut and nuts. Blend in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into 9 x 13 in pan. Bake at 350 degrees about 30 minutes. Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: chicken bundles
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese, milk, dill weed, salt and pepper until smooth.
Stir in chicken, celery and onions.
Unroll crescent roll dough and separate into 12 rectangles, 4 from each tube.
Press perforations together.
Spoon 1/3 cup of the chicken mixture into the center of each rectangle.
Bring edges up to the center and pinch to seal. Brush with butter and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: demon cake
directions: Melt the chocolate over simmering water.
Cream together the butter and 2
1/4 cups sugar.
Add the melted chocolate to this mixture.
Sift the flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add well beaten egg yolks and stiffly beaten
egg
whites
to
mixture. Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour the
batter
into three well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at	350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken superb(diabetic)
directions: Mix together flour, salt and half the pepper.
Lightly coat chicken with flour mixture.
Cook chicken in margarine until golden, using a tightly covered pan.
Turn breasts meat side down; add remaining ingredients and cover.
Stirring occasionally, simmer gently until tender (about 30 minutes).
Serve over noodles or rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt into the Cool Whip; spoon into crust.
Freeze firm for 4 hours.
Remove from freezer for 30 minutes before serving. Garnish with strawberries or use any kind of yogurt.

title: penuche
directions: Mix sugars, cream, milk and butter in saucepan.
Boil to soft stage or 238°, stirring only if needed.
Remove from heat.
Cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Add vanilla.
Beat vigorously until fudge thickens and loses gloss.
Add nuts. Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Score; cut when firm.

title: bacon-corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain.
Saute onion in drippings for about 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and mix to a smooth paste. Gradually add water and stir until smooth.
Add potatoes, celery and bay leaves.
Cover and cook over low heat.
Blend in corn, milk, seasonings and bacon.
Heat and serve.

title: tri-berry salad
directions: Mix both jello packages with 1 cup of boiling water.
Add thawed berries.
Mix well and add cranberry sauce.
Chill and serve.

title: seedless grape salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix pineapple with grapes.
Make sauce of pineapple juice, sour cream and brown sugar.

title: creamy broccoli soup au gratin
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add water and contents of rice and seasoning packets.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Combine flour and dry mustard in a small bowl.
Gradually add about 1/2 cup broth, stirring until smooth. Stir remaining broth, flour mixture and milk into rice mixture. Heat to simmer stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese.
Sprinkle with green onion.

title: sheryl stuff
directions: Spray pan with pam and add all stuff.
Cook until tender.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat together 2 minutes in mixer the eggs, cake mix, lemon jello and water.
Add oil and beat 1 minute.
Pour into 10 x 14-inch oiled pan or 2 shallow pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Save liquid from asparagus, melt butter and blend in flour and salt. Add liquid and cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Alternate layers of hard-boiled eggs, asparagus and cheese sauce.
Cover with bread crumbs in greased casserole.
Sprinkle paprika over crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 8.

title: praline pumpkin pie
directions: Cream the oleo with 1/3 cup brown sugar; stir in pecans. Press evenly in a layer in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool 10 minutes on wire rack.
Lower oven temperature to 350°.

title: franklin's chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in water until done.
Remove chicken from broth and debone.
Add chicken back to broth and add rice and soup.
Add seasonings.
Cover and cook until rice is done, using medium heat, and then turn gradually to low heat on top of range.

title: tex-mex cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl and into a hot greased 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown (more golden than brown).

title: lemon-honey chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Beat egg yolks and combine with honey, salt, lemon rind and juice in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring until mixture starts to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Cool, stirring occasionally.
When cooled completely, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour in pie shell.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: donut muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour with
baking
powder, salt and spices.
Mix alternately with milk.
Fill
greased muffin tins 2/3 full.	Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove and roll in 6 tablespoons melted butter, then in 1 cup confectioners sugar.

title: hot mustard sauce for dipping
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Keeps in refrigerator.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, reserving a small amount of stuffing for topping.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream together in a large bowl the butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water according to package directions.
Drain broccoli and spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise, mushrooms, curry powder and 1/2 cup grated cheese in a medium bowl. Spread chicken mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over top.

title: buffet beef cubes
directions: Shake beef in bag with flour.
Brown in electric or regular 10-inch fry
pan.
Combine next 7 ingredients and add to browned meat.
Add onions and bay leaf.
Cook.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours until tender and liquid is of gravy consistency.
Serve over hot rice, seasoned with butter and parsley over buttered noodles or mashed potatoes.
Discard bay leaf.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl.
Make 3 depressions.
Into one, pour vinegar, into another vanilla and into the other, pour the oil.
Pour cold water over all and mix.
Do not beat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch ungreased pan.

title: easy apple dumplings
directions: Place half of apple in center of square.
Put on top of apple 1 teaspoon oleo, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bring up points of square to top of apple and moisten as needed to seal. Place on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to butter mixture.
Mix until smooth. Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix all in top of double boiler except vanilla.
Beat one minute to blend.
Cook over boiling water for 7 minutes.
Add vanilla; don't overcook.
Beat 2 more minutes.

title: berry lite mousse
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water in blender at low speed until gelatin is dissolved, about 30 seconds. Add ice. Stir until partially melted.
Add strawberries.
Blend well.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour into dessert glasses.
Chill about 2 hours. Garnish. Makes 6 servings.
Contains less than 45 calories.

title: hot vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together, then stir in the mayonnaise.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Brown the Ritz crumbs in the margarine, then spread the crumbs over the vegetable mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes, or until heated through and bubbling.
Serves about 8 to 10.

title: heavenly hushpuppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add enough buttermilk until mixture has a coarse consistency.
In a large pot heat vegetable oil to 325 degrees. (Try to maintain a constant temperature.)
Spoon mixture into hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed (drain). Pour Italian dressing over noodles and serve chilled.

title: ham strata(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Trim crust off bread when bread is dried.
Place bread in cookie sheet, covering whole bottom.
Sprinkle grated cheese (1/2 pound) on top of bread, then all ham on top of cheese.
Then sprinkle remaining cheese on top of ham.
Beat eggs together, then add rest of ingredients to egg mixture.
Mix well and pour over cheese and ham.
Cover pan with foil; refrigerate overnight or 6 hours minimum.
Bake at 325° for 50 or 60 minutes, uncovered. Cool 10 to 15 minutes before slicing.

title: london broil
directions: Score meat, combine marinade and pour over meat. Cover and let stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours. Turn several times.

title: first lady's pralines
directions: Blend sugar, salt and evaporated milk.
Cook to 232° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, butter and pecan halves.
Beat just until candy begins to thicken.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper
(work fast for candy hardens quickly).
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and flour.
Add eggs, corn and milk.
Add baking powder just before baking.
Bake in a 325°oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Will serve 8.
(I bake in a lasagna pan.)

title: old fashioned cream of tomato soup
directions: In a saucepan, combine the first six ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Heat cream in the top of double boiler over simmering water; add to the tomato mixture just before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: browned rice
directions: Brown onions, rice and beef in oleo in large skillet.
Place in a large baking dish and add other remaining ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: keebler 15 minute cherry burst pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla. Mix until well blended. Fold in remaining ingredients one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Mound mixture into crust. Freeze until firm, about 2 to 3 hours. Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.

title: creamy green beans
directions: Remove wrappers from green bean boxes; place boxes in a flat baking dish and pierce with a fork.
Microwave at High for 12 to 15 minutes, rearranging boxes once.
Drain beans and place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and microwave at High for 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yield:
8 servings (about 35 calories per serving).

title: canzadia's fruit salad
directions: Cut up the fruit and nuts.

title: quick dinner
directions: Saute beef and onions (until cooked) in pan.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with can of English peas.
Put potatoes on top of peas.
Cook 20 minutes in 350° oven.
About 5 minutes before you take out, sprinkle with cheese.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Stir cream cheese until very soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 1/2 cups milk and lemon instant pudding mix.
Beat slowly with mixer 1 minute.
Pour at once into a cooled, baked graham cracker crust.
Chill 1 hour or until firm.

title: bar b q sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a
boiler.
Simmer
for	20 minutes. This will not burn easily
if
used
on
meat cooked on grill. Good on poultry, beef or pork.

title: sweet 'n sour hot sauce pape'
directions: * Adjust to taste.

title: fillet of sole oscar
directions: Wash, drain and dry fillets.
Cut into serving portions. Place 2 stalks asparagus on each portion of fish and roll up jelly roll style and secure with toothpick.
Place in baking dish sprayed with butter-flavored Pam (11 x 13 x 2-inch casserole or whatever size will hold number of fillets preparing).
Sprinkle with lemon juice and dot lightly with butter or margarine.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until fish is opaque and flakes easily.
Pour sauce over the fish and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer until hot and bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: lambert's throwed rolls
directions: Combine sugar and yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until yeast begins to foam.
Thoroughly mix milk, butter, sugar, eggs and salt in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in the yeast mixture and 3 1/2 cups of flour, adding a bit more if necessary to make a soft, pliable dough.
Turn dough out on a floured board and let rest while you clean and butter a bowl. Knead dough gently for 4 to 5 minutes, adding flour, until the dough is smooth and silky.
Return the dough to the bowl; cover with plastic wrap and let rise in a warm place until the dough is doubled in size.
Butter a 12 cup muffin pan.
Punch down dough; pinch off pieces about 1 1/2-inches in diameter or enough to fill 1/2 of muffin cup and roll into smooth spheres.
Place two such pieces in each prepared muffin cups.
(It should be a tight fit.) Cover dough loosely with plastic wrap for 45 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake rolls 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown. Serve as soon as they cool enough to throw.
Makes 12 thrown rolls.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Fry the onion and the chicken. Mix the chicken, onions, cream of chicken soup, sour cream and chili powder in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
Mix the two cheeses together in a bowl.
Lay out tortillas.
Spoon 2 heaping tablespoons of the chicken mixture into the tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll tortilla. Repeat this step until you have used all the tortillas.
Put the tortillas into a large baking dish.
Pour the remaining mixture over top of the rolled tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook, uncovered, at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in oven at 500° for 30 minutes (do not preheat). Add soups and water; cover pan and cook 2 hours at 325°.
Add vegetables; cook additional hour at 325°.
Serve; use sauce for gravy.

title: fruit punch
directions: Shortly before serving, empty frozen fruit juice concentrates, pineapple juice, cranberry juice and cold water into large punch bowl.
Stir to hasten thawing.
Just before serving, gently pour in ginger ale and sparkling water.
Float fruited ice ring on top. Makes 50 servings.

title: gummy gooey cake
directions: Mix together.
This will be stiff.
Spread evenly in a long pan.

title: world's best roast
directions: Use deep, long pan.
Line with foil.
Place roast in bottom. Cover with onion slices and mushrooms.
Pour soup over roast.
Add vegetables.
Cook at 225° to 250° overnight at least 8 hours.

title: veal chops and squash
directions: Combine flour, salt, garlic and basil.
Roll chops in mixture. Brown chops in a large frying pan.
Pour off drippings.
Add 1/2 cup of water.
Cover and cook 45 minutes.
Drain tomatoes to make 1 cup.
Combine remaining flour mixture with tomato liquid and stir into cooking liquid.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and zucchini and cook, covered, 20 minutes.

title: french fruit au gratin
directions: Mix fruits and cognac and let marinate for 2 hours at room temperature.
Pour mixture into 2-quart shallow baking dish.
In saucepan, mix egg yolks, sugar and cream and stir over low heat until thickened.
Do not boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture evenly over undrained marinated fruit.
Place under preheated broiler and broil 8 to 10 minutes or until fluffy and golden brown. Serve warm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken surprise
directions: In large skillet, cook chicken and onion.
Add broccoli florets, mushrooms and mushroom soup with 1 cup milk.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Cover with sharp cheese.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift and stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Chill dough for 2 hours. Roll in small balls and drop in mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place balls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 8-10 min.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Beat in cream cheese until fluffy. Alternately add cocoa and flour.
Add eggs.
Begin and end with flour when mixing.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Combine cake mix and butter. Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping. Add brown sugar and cinnamon to this reserved topping.
Mix well and set aside.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, all your seasonings and onion.
Add tomato paste, sauce, tomatoes and water.
Add bell pepper.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: cheesy yummies
directions: Mix cheese with butter. Add flour until well mixed.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Blend into mixture; add flavor.
Bake in greased pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Do not open oven for 1 hour.

title: cucumbers with pasta
directions: Peel and seed the cucumbers.
Dice the flesh into 1/4-inch pieces and toss with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 2 tablespoons wine vinegar.
Let set for 30 minutes and drain.
Peel, seed and dice the tomatoes and combine with the cucumbers, onions, garlic, herbs and olive oil.
Taste and add more vinegar, salt and pepper if necessary.
Boil the spaghetti in several quarts of salted water until cooked through, but still chewy.
Toss the hot pasta with the cucumber-tomato mixture, serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: strawberry salad mold
directions: Make gelatin and let cool until syrupy.
Add softened cream cheese, drained pineapple and nuts.
Put into mild and chill to set.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over low heat. Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted. Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies and additional flavorings, if desired. Stir until well coated. Press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2 pan coated with cooking spray. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches) with shortening.
Heat margarine and 1 package chocolate chips in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except nuts and 1/2 cup chocolate chips real hard with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Spread in pan with a rubber spatula.
Bake until the center is set, about 30 minutes.
Cool completely; cut into 1 3/4 x 1 1/2-inch brownies.
Store brownies tightly covered.
Makes 20 brownies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops; drain fat.
Put onion soup, flour and 2 cups water
in
pan.
Add
pork chops, carrots and potatoes; sprinkle with thyme.
Cook
on simmer in electric frypan until carrots are ready, about 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add very slowly sugar and continue to beat. Fold in dates and nuts. Drop batter on well greased cookie sheet. Put in oven and turn oven off. Leave overnight or at least 2 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix water, 100% bran, shortening and sugar together and let cool.
Mix and add eggs, flour, soda, buttermilk and bran flakes. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: apple butter - no sugar
directions: Put all ingredients into large saucepan and simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes.
Apples should be soft.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Put half in blender and blend until smooth.
Blend the other half.
Keeps well in refrigerator or freeze.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix all together and heat.

title: vanilla cream pie or pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; cool.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: pomander in a pot
directions: In
a
saucepan,
cover spices with water and warm over low heat.
Check occasionally and add more water as needed.

title: broccoli marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least one hour.

title: filet belmont house
directions: Season steaks with salt and pepper to taste.
Grill 4 minutes per side.
Mix broth, brandy and rosemary and boil (about 5 minutes).
Spoon over steaks and top with Blue cheese.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan. Add onion; saute until soft and transparent. Stir in ketchup, water, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, vinegar, tomato paste, dry mustard and red pepper. Stirring occasionally, simmer uncovered 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Immediately stir shrimp into sauce, covering completely. Let stand 15 minutes.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Place the chicken breasts in a casserole dish with a pat of butter on each breast.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over top. Bake covered for 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
This is called Sunday Chicken because it cooks while you are at church.
Pour over rice when done and serve.

title: ada's baked beans
directions: Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour or longer at 350°.

title: butter pecan fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk.
Heat to boiling point and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add chips, pecans, marshmallows and vanilla. Stir until marshmallows melt. Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix macaroni and cheese as usual according to the box directions.
Add the soup.
Add the chopped mango.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.

title: salsa
directions: Finely chop tomatoes, garlic, cilantro, jalapeno (use jalapeno only, no juice) and onions.
Mix together in bowl and refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips.
The salsa gets hotter when it is refrigerated.
Do not add more jalapenos than the recipe calls for.

title: zucchini dressing
directions: Mix stuffing according to directions on box. Add chopped celery. Then slice and peel squash.
In a greased baking dish, layer squash and stuffing.
Beat egg and cream of mushroom soup together and pour over top. Bake at 350° for about 40 to 50 minutes or until squash is done.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Mix spinach and cottage cheese; set aside.
Brown turkey, onion and garlic, then add chilies, tomato sauce, bread crumbs, chili powder and cumin.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan: tortillas, 1/3 meat, 1/3 spinach and 1/3 cheese.
Repeat until done.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes covered and 10 minutes uncovered.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into small meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for another 30 to 40 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt butter with spices and Worcestershire sauce.
Combine cereals in roaster.
Pour butter mixture over cereals; cover and bake at 250° for one hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake another 30 minutes.
Add nuts.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: annie floye's strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs thoroughly.
Beat one egg at a time into the mixture.
Bake in 3 cake pans (8-inches) for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: broccoli salad(easy, delightful, cold summer salad)
directions: Steam broccoli flowerheads until just crisp.
Add Feta cheese. Pour vinaigrette dressing over all.
Serve warm or cold.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, eggs, jam and milk together, then add dry ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in Bundt pan.

title: crab and cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 2 hours. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: never fail bake turkey
directions: Massage bird with salt and pepper inside and out.
Peel peeled onion and chopped celery inside the cavity of turkey.
Add water to roasting pan.
Place turkey back side up in roaster on a rack and put lid on roaster, fitting tightly.
Place covered roaster in a cold oven and turn to bake at 500°.
Do not open oven door at any time.
Let cook for one hour.
Turn off the oven and forget the turkey for several hours.
Meat will be brown and moist and plenty of broth.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Steam or cook vegetables in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Combine soup base and milk (enough for a good soup base consistency).
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Heat (not too long).
Put in bowls and top with Colby.

title: gladys' polish mistakes
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; add salt to taste.
Drain.
Add oregano.
Chunk the Velveeta cheese.
Add cheese to meat mixture; mix well while meat is hot so cheese will melt.
Spread on rye bread.
Can freeze on cookie sheet, then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Use 2 heaping tablespoonfuls to 1 cup boiling water.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients, fold in frozen blueberries.
Allow to sit several hours.
Serve in baked pie shell, tart shells or in sherbet dishes with no crust.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: savannah sunshine cake
directions: Stir together pineapple, apple pie filling, cinnamon mix and raisins. Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8 cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture. Slice cold butter into squares and place on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Resift 2 cups flour with powdered sugar into medium bowl.
Add butter and mix thoroughly.
Pat dough evenly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake until golden, about 25 minutes.

title: broasted new potatoes
directions: Pour oil into plastic bag. Add potatoes and shake to coat well. Add dressing mix and shake well until all potatoes are coated. Place potatoes in crock-pot and cook 8 hours on low or 4 hours on high.

title: almond gingersnaps(skurna pepperkakor)
directions: Work butter until creamy.
Add sugar, molasses, spices, baking soda, almonds and flour.
Turn onto floured baking board and knead until smooth.
Shape into 2 thick slightly flattened rolls.
Wrap each in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Cut crosswise with sharp knife in thin slices.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) 8 to 10 minutes.

title: apple potato meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; turn into foil-lined loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turn into serving dish.
Serves 6.

title: kitchenette cake
directions: Sift in bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add the shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add the egg and beat 2 more minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan in a 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up.
Mix all together and put in large casserole or loaf cake pan.
Cover with crushed potato chips if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: three chocolate fudge
directions: In a a large saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rapid boil, boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat, stir in marshmallows until melted.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add chocolate bars and baking chocolate, stir until melted.
Fold in vanilla and pecans, mix well.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1 in. baking pan.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: possum pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Spread onto bottom of crust. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. In another bowl, combine pudding mixes. Add milk and vanilla. Beat on low speed for 2 minutes. Spoon over the pecans. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Top with whipped cream and pecan halves.

title: congealed beet salad
directions: Bring water, beet juice, vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Pour over jello.
When jello begins to set, add beets and seed.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: beef patty and peppers
directions: Coat patty with flour.
Place on large pieces of foil or in small foil pan.
Place pepper strips around meat.
Sprinkle with soy sauce, sherry and pepper.
Seal or cover tightly.
Bake in 400°
oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 serving.
Good with potato nuggets sprinkled with garlic or onion powder (1 cup) and sliced tomato and lettuce.

title: yule cake
directions: Place nuts, dates, cherries and raisins in a large bowl. Measure flour, baking powder and salt into sifter.
Sift over nuts and fruit; mix well.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add 5 cups powdered sugar and mix.
Will be stiff.
Roll into balls.
Melt the chocolate chips. Dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper.
Keep cold.

title: cream cheese olive dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk slowly to achieve dipping consistency. Chill and serve with potato chips or Ritz crackers.

title: gourmet chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal in blender to a fine powder.
Cream butter and both sugars together.
Add eggs, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix together flour, blended oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add chips, grated Hershey bar and nuts.

title: baked beans
directions: Place all ingredients in large skillet and cook on low 20 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Mix oregano, basil, onion flakes, cheese and bread crumbs in a mixing bowl.
Dip chicken into butter, then into bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine apple juice, onion and remaining margarine. After 45 minutes, pour over chicken and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: my grandmother's scones
directions: Grease 12 bun tins.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar.
Beat egg and milk together.
Pour into flour.
Mix until creamy.
Fill bun tins about 2/3 full.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend and chill for 1 hour.
Use pears, apples, grapes and melons of all kinds.
Cut in bite size pieces.
Arrange around bowl of dip.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Drain off liquid.
Combine sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add celery seed.
Put cucumbers and onions in plastic freezer containers; pour syrup on top.
Close tightly and freeze.

title: creamed broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in salt water in saucepan.
Drain.
In saucepan melt butter, blend in flour, add milk, salt, pepper, and cook until thickened.
Add onions to drained broccoli and then combine onion and broccoli to cream sauce.
Beat until light.
Place in baking dish.
Top with crumbs and cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: saucy budget steak
directions: Brown shoulder or steak in preheated 425° oven 20 minutes; drain fat.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Combine water, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire and salt.
Pour over meat.
Cover; bake until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Spoon sauce over meat.
Can be made ahead, refrigerated and reheated, covered.

title: olives in cheese
directions: Mix the cheese and sauce.
Add enough cream to make a smooth, thick paste.
Roll olive in cream mixture.
Be sure that each is well coated.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: fried oysters
directions: Roll oysters in cracker crumbs or corn meal.
Melt fat in a skillet or heavy frying pan.
Add oysters and sprinkle with salt. Fry on medium heat until a golden brown on both sides.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a small bowl mix the Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar together to make a dressing. Combine all the veggies, cheese and bacon. Add the dressing and mix well. Refrigerate and serve.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Rub with garlic and thyme.
Brown in hot oil. Combine 2 tablespoons juice with cornstarch.
Combine honey and mustard.
Stir in skillet with remaining juice.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.	Stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices.
Add pineapple.
Cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens.
Serves 4.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple and combine for 3/4 cup liquid.
Mix together in a saucepan the sugar, vinegar and 1/2 cup of the combined fruit juices; add cloves and cinnamon stick. Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes over low heat.
Mix the flour with the balance of the combined fruit juices and blend into the hot syrup.
Stirring constantly, cook until smooth and thickened.
Add cherries, pineapple and lemon juice and heat until hot.
Serve the sauce hot with hot or cold ham.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: De-cap strawberries and wash.
Place berries in colander. Pour boiling water over them completely, then spray (or rinse) with cold water thoroughly.
Place in a large pot and add 2 cups of sugar and juice from half of a lemon.
Turn stove on high, stirring until juice is a rolling boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove. Add 2 cups more of sugar.
Bring to a rolling boil again 5 minutes. Pour in a large bowl.
Let stand 2 days. Remove white residue from top. Stir every so often.
Boil jars.
Add preserves and put a paraffin layer on top.
Let set, then paraffin layer again.
Put on lid.

title: fudgy no-bakes
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa, milk, and butter or margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Add oats and vanilla.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto was paper, forming slightly with fingers, if needed.
Cool completely.
Makes approximately 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: southern tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, milk and dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Place dough on lightly floured surface.
Sprinkle a little flour over dough and roll to about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Prick tops with fork and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned on top.

title: caramel candy
directions: Put all ingredients (except vanilla and walnuts) into stainless steel pan.
Boil 20 minutes.
(Do not overboil.) Add nuts and vanilla and pour in greased pan.

title: rose petal jam
directions: In a large stockpot, combine sugar and water over medium-high heat; stir constantly until sugar dissolves.
Stir petals and rose flower water into syrup.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Add pectin; stir until dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil again and boil 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat; skim off foam.
If desired, tint with food coloring.
Pour into jars.
Cool and store in refrigerator.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Break crackers coarsely into one pie shell.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan; boil 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers, dot with oleo and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add top crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add to beaten eggs.
Add lemon juice and apricot juice and cook to medium sauce.
When cooled, place layers of apricots, cheese and nuts in bowl.
Pour sauce over all. Chill.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt. Boil butter, cocoa and water.
Mix together eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Mix all three parts together.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in a greased sheet pan.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Drain carrots; arrange carrots, bell pepper and onions in layers in container. Make marinade of other ingredients and beat well.
Pour over and refrigerate.
Will keep for weeks.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread beans on a 10-inch serving platter.
Blend sour cream and salad dressing mix; spread over beans.
Layer remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos; put one layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. (Save some of the crushed Oreos to sprinkle on top of cake.)
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla; pour over crushed Oreos.
Mix the cream cheese and margarine until smooth, then mix in powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Put this mixture over the pudding mixture.
Put remaining crushed Oreos on top.

title: orange pork chops
directions: Trim fat and brown chops in oil.
Remove chops and keep drippings.
Add onion and saute.
Return chops to pan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover skillet and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Remove cover; increase heat to medium-high and continue to cook until liquid is almost evaporated, about 3 minutes.

title: frozen oreo pie
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies finely.
Stir in melted butter.
Pat cookies flat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice softened ice cream to fit in pan evenly.
May decorate top with extra cookie sprinkles or whole cookies.
Freeze.
Serve slightly thawed.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix preceding ingredients together and pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, salt and pepper to taste.
Save half of dressing mix for top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: frankfurter pizzas
directions: Place muffin halves on paper plate.
Spread cut sides with equal amount of pizza sauce.
Carefully make 5 cups into frankfurters 3/4-inch apart and almost through.
Arrange frankfurter in a circle on each muffin half.
Cover with half slice of cheese.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Microwave on High 1 minute.

title: summer melon chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients with mayonnaise except lettuce and melon slices.
Place lettuce leaves on plate.
Place melon slices on lettuce.
Fill circle of melon with chicken melon salad.

title: meat-za-pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in pie plate with fork.
Press 1/2-inch from top of pan.
Spread catsup on meat, then mushrooms, cheese and oregano.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple loaf
directions: Combine apples, pecans and sugar.
Let stand one hour, stirring often; do not drain.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and spices.
Stir in butter, vanilla and eggs.
Spoon into 2 greased 1 pound coffee cans.
Tie a 2-inch band of foil around top of cans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center is clean.
Cool in cans for 10 minutes.
Remove from cans and complete cooling.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Slice the smoked sausage and place in the bottom of an electric skillet or baking dish.
Top with sliced potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning and cook until done.
Do not stir while cooking.
Easy and delicious!

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Cream mayonnaise and sugar; blend well.
Add flour and water.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over low flame.
Pour over sugar and mix.
Add eggs and flour which has been sifted, vanilla and chopped nuts.
Put in greased pan (about 7 x 10-inch); bake very slowly for about 30 minutes in oven at 350°.
Cut into squares when taken from oven.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Yields about 30.

title: sugarless applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins and dates in 2 cups water until water is evaporated.
Watch carefully!
Combine all dry ingredients and add raisins and dates.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mad hatter meatballs
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add green pepper and onion and cook until tender.
Stir in soups and water.
Heat to boiling, then turn down heat and simmer sauce, stirring occasionally.
While sauce cooks, make meatballs.
Beat egg slightly in large bowl.
Add ground beef, bread, evaporated milk and salt.
Mix well.
Shape meat into balls about the size of ping pong balls.
Drop balls into simmering sauce and cook slowly about 1 hour or until sauce has thickened.
Can serve over rice or mashed potatoes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn with basil
directions: Melt oleo in 3-quart saucepan.
Saute onions and pepper until tender (5 minutes).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat through. Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: quick refrigerator relish
directions: Combine all of the ingredients. Place in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours before serving.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Put chicken in paper sack with Bisquick, salt, paprika and pepper.
Shake until chicken is well coated.
Use shortening to coat sides of baking pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake for 45 minutes in 425° oven.
Turn chicken over and bake 15 minutes longer.
Last 15 minutes, put 1/2 cup water and cover with aluminum foil.

title: salsa and cheese
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Pour the jar of salsa over the cream cheese and enjoy with Fritos or tortilla chips.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Make pudding with milk in a bowl until thick.
In separate bowl, mix boiling water with Jell-O, then add strawberries.
In separate bowl, break bread in pieces.
In large bowl, layer cake, Jell-O, pudding, Cool Whip until gone.
Cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: hash browns
directions: Peel potatoes and cut up or shred.
Combine potatoes, onion, salt and pepper in a large skillet with melted butter.
Cook over medium heat about 10 minutes, until bottom is crisp.
Turn over and cook 10 more minutes.

title: veggie pizza appetizer
directions: Pam a 13 x 15-inch baking sheet.
Unroll rolls and spread them out to fit pan as a crust.
Bake according to package directions; let cool.

title: grilled kielbasa sausage and potatoes
directions: Slice sausage into 1/2-inch sections.
Cut potatoes in half; slice into thin pieces.
Place in pan with sausage; cover with pieces of margarine.
Sprinkle diced onion on top to season. Cover with foil; place on grill.
Gently turn frequently to prevent potatoes from sticking.
Cook for approximately 30 to 45 minutes, until potatoes become soft.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat eggs. Combine with milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix thoroughly with milk mixture. Heat deep fat in heavy skillet. Pour batter through funnel into fat. Move funnel to make different shapes.
If batter is too stiff, add milk. If too thin, add flour. When cake is golden brown, drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Saute clams in butter and oil and garlic for 3 minutes or so. Add remainder of ingredients except cornstarch.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add cornstarch, which was mixed with 2 teaspoons water and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Thin with reserved juice if too thick.
This will be enough sauce for a one pound package of linguini or spaghetti.
Recipe is easily cut in half.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Pour into squash mixture and add eggs and milk.
Beginning with squash, layer into casserole dish.
Then layer either crumbled or whole saltine crackers and grated Cheddar cheese.
Make at least 2 layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
