Onion or grated carrot may also be added to this.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix ingredients in order, stirring well after each addition. Pour in a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook at 350° about 30 to 45 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Do not mix any of these ingredients! Place ingredients in pan in layers as they are called for, starting with the pineapple and ending with cut up butter on the top.
Place in preheated oven and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.

title: lorraine's german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cool, peel and slice them in a large bowl. Add chopped onion.
Add sugar.
Cook diced bacon until crisp. Pour over potatoes, onion and sugar.
Bring to boil the vinegar. Pour over potatoes.
Mix.
If you need more vinegar, add 1/4 cup at a time.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put all ingredients
into a blender (with top on) for 10 seconds at high speed.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger (drain).
Add taco mix, tomato sauce and olives; simmer.
Spread out crescent rolls.
Spread 1/2 crushed chips.
Pour hamburger mix over.
Spread sour cream over top. Spread shredded cheese.
Cover with remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: easy crock pot mac and cheese
directions: Add all ingredients into a lightly greased crock pot.
Cover and cook on high 2-3 hours.
Stir once or twice.

title: orange diet (sugar-free) salad
directions: Drain the oranges; combine with other ingredients except Jell-O.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over the mixture.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: blender pie
directions: Put all in blender and mix well.
Grease and flour a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour all into pie plate and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until solid and brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta with 3 colored peppers
directions: In saute pan, place margarine, oil and onion.
On medium-high heat, saute onions until translucent.
Add all peppers and cook on medium-high until tender but not mushy.
Stir gently.
Add salt and pepper and cream.
Mix gently.
Cook, uncovered, until reduced in half.
Add a dash of white wine.

title: shrimp christmas tree
directions: Place frozen shrimp in salted boiling water.
Let the shrimp return to boil.
Cook from 2 to 3 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain and chill.
Separate and wash endive.
Drain well.
Chill.
Place cone in the center of the styrofoam square and draw a circle around the base of cone.
Cut out the circle and insert cone.
Cover base and cone with overlapping leaves of endive.
Fasten endive to styrofoam with toothpick halves.
Start at the outside edge of the base and work up.
Cover fully with greens to resemble Christmas tree.
Attach shrimp to tree with toothpicks.
Add cherry tomatoes with toothpick around cone to look like ornaments.
Provide cocktail sauce for dunking.

title: low cholesterol blueberry muffins
directions: Combine and sift 1 3/4 cups flour, sugar and baking powder. Combine milk, Scramblers and oil; beat with rotary beaters until well mixed.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Pour liquids into well.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not overmix.

title: christmas salad
directions: Prepare jello with boiling water and cold water.
Add pineapple.
Pour into 9 x 12 dish and refrigerate until set.
To the cream cheese (room temperature), add milk and mix until like soft butter.
Spread over lime jello and chill thoroughly.

title: fresh pineapple and macadamia nut pie
directions: Twist crown from pineapple and cut the pineapple into quarters. Remove fruit from shells. Core and cut pineapple into bite size chunks.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon peel and nutmeg in a large saucepan. Stir in water and food coloring. Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is clear and thickened. Remove from heat.
Add pineapple.
Cool.
Spoon fruit into baked pie shell or Macadamia Nut Crust.
Pour sauce evenly over fruit. Cover and chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, flour, milk and butter. Bring to a full boil.
Boil for three minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool completely.

title: hog maw(pig stomach)
directions: Dice the raw potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix sausage, salt, potatoes and onion.
Stuff pig stomach.
Sew up the opening. Place in a roast pan with 1/4 cup of water.
Cover.
Bake 3 hours at 300° (uncover for 1 hour).
I use 1 1/2 pounds spareribs.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook hamburger.
Season with salt, pepper, chili powder (optional) and garlic salt.
In a separate pan, fry tortillas in deep fat; very short time to make tortillas soft and pliable.
Dip tortillas in sauce.
Lay tortillas in pan.
Fill with meat, onions, olives, cheese and sauce.
Turn over so seam is on the bottom. Continue this step until pan is filled.
Pour or spoon sauce over top of enchiladas.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 1 dozen.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add cheese, mushroom soup and milk. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove and add olives and cashews, if you prefer.
Stir into mixture and top with a can of Chinese noodles.
Return and bake 15 minutes.

title: fig preserves
directions: Cook sugar and vinegar until boiling.
Drop in figs; try not to stir very much.
Cook until syrupy.

title: instant russian tea
directions: In large bowl combine first 3 ingredients (dry) with spices. Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons (more of less to taste) for each cup of boiling water.
Makes about 30 servings.
Yields 2 1/2 cups dry mix.

title: mamaw johnson's nut loaf cake
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups together (no water added).
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread chicken evenly over soup.
Mix stuffing according to directions, using chicken broth instead of water. Spread over the chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: prize winning zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Mix in flour, spices, baking powder and soda.
Stir in pineapple and zucchini until well mixed.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: In saucepan combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Place on medium heat.
Stir until butter and sugar are melted and dissolved.
Bring to a boil one minute.
Remove from heat. Quickly add peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Mix well and drop on waxed paper or cookie sheet by the teaspoonful.
Cookies will become firm in a few minutes.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix cereal with margarine.
Beat sugar into eggs; add cereal mixture and remaining ingredients, blending well.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish; place in pan of hot water.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir thoroughly.
Bake 20 minutes longer, or until knife inserted 1-inch from center comes out clean.
Serve warm or cool with whipped cream.

title: ruth's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to rolling boil.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Make into 1-inch balls.
Place in freezer on cookie sheet.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Heat milk; pour in juice of cherries.
Add marshmallows.
When dissolved, crumble in graham crackers.
Add raisins, coconut and nuts.
Pour into tube pan lined with waxed paper.
Decorate with cherries and nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: california icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix fruits, nuts and crumbs.
In double boiler or microwave, melt marshmallows with milk.
Cool.
Pour into dry ingredients. Makes 3 wax paper lined loaf pans or 1 tube pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Panboil first 3 ingredients. Mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole.
Add more crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, garlic and pepper.
Arrange chicken in a shallow casserole or baking pan; pour on the lemon mixture.
Cover and bake 40 minutes or until tender, basting occasionally.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer to brown.
To serve, sprinkle with chopped parsley. Yields 4 servings.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Add cheese (cubed) and chili.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve with crackers, tortilla chips (Eagle white corn rounds) or Dorito chips.

title: rice pilaf(yields 6 servings)
directions: Saute onion, noodles and rice in butter until lightly toasted. Add water, garlic, cinnamon and orange slices.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook, covered, for 40 to 45 minutes.
(Do not lift lid during cooking.)

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Scald milk with sugar and salt.
In bowl, mix cornstarch with cold water.
Add to scalded milk until slightly thickened.
Add flavoring.
Serve on plain white cake, plum or carrot pudding.

title: nasi goreng
directions: Fry onions in oil until tender.
Add meat and cooked rice and stir until well mixed.
Add Worcestershire sauce, curry powder, salt and pepper; stir until hot.
Make well in center of rice and break eggs into it.
Stir eggs until partly scrambled; then mix rice into it.
Stir until well blended.
Serve on platter surrounded by 2 tomatoes, thinly sliced.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare raw rice and frozen broccoli according to directions but without salt. Melt butter or margarine with the onions. Heat only until butter is completely melted.
Pour this mixture into a long Pyrex dish. Add the cooked rice, cheese and soup and mix well.
Drain the cooked broccoli and spread it over the rice mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: maple and brown sugar meat loaf
directions: Mix sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard until sugar is dissolved.
Combine ground beef, oatmeal, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup of tomato sauce mixture; blend thoroughly.
Shape into an oval loaf and turn into shallow pan.
Pour remaining sauce mixture on top of loaf.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour, basting occasionally.

title: four layer delight
directions: Cream oleo, salt, flour and pecans with a fork.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
For second layer, cream sugar, cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Using low speed, mix pudding with milk until thick.
Spread over second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in a greased shallow baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with milk or whipping cream.

title: mom's fruit salad
directions: Make pudding using juice from pineapple chunks to equal 1 1/2 c.	If short of juice, add a little lemon juice.
Cool slightly. Mix in all other ingredients.

title: creole sauce
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Add onion, green pepper, celery and garlic and saute over medium heat until tender; do not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato puree, bay leaf, thyme, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Taste for seasoning.
May need some sugar to cut acidity of tomato products.
Add shrimp, scallops or any other seafood item.

title: scallopini of veal avocado(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Pound the scallops until thin.
Rub flour lightly into each piece of meat.
Cut the avocado in half lengthwise, peel and remove the seed.
Cut the halves lengthwise into thin slices and coat with lemon juice to keep from discoloring.
Heat 3 tablespoons of butter in a heavy skillet and add a drop of Wesson oil (this will keep the butter from burning too quickly).
Add the scallops and saute over medium heat until golden brown.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove the scallops to a platter and keep in a warm place.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat.
Bake in 2 loaf pans for 30 minutes.

title: old-timey pickles
directions: Wash and cut large cucumbers.
Pack into clean jars.
Add to each quart jar 1 teaspoon salt and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Fill each jar 1/3 full of vinegar.
Finish filling jar with water; shake to dissolve salt and sugar.
After sealing, put into hot water bath for 10 minutes after water starts to boil, then remove at once. Check to see that jars are sealed.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute celery
and
onion in butter in a large Dutch oven until tender.
Add
potatoes,
water, bouillon cubes, seasoned salt, rosemary,
garlic
powder
and
black pepper.
Cover and simmer about
20 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat and mash potatoes.
Add milk and cheese; cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Yields 10 cups.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare the cake according to the package directions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let the cake cook, then pierce it with a fork and drizzle the Kahlua over the cake.
Chill overnight.

title: old-fashioned molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter until soft.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Add buttermilk and flour ingredients alternately; beat until smooth after each addition. Drop batter from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes.

title: smothered potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes and along with onions brown quickly in small amount of grease in skillet.
After browning, add enough water to cover, cover and simmer until tender.
Add water if they cook down and are not quite soft enough.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare crust; do not cook.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Stir together flour, salt, sugar and cocoa in large bowl. Add butter, eggs and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Spread batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle hot cake with marshmallows.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil sliced carrots in boiling, salted water until tender. Alternate carrots, pepper and onion slices.
Mix dressing well. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Cut bread in small squares.
Mix everything except sugar and nuts.
Pour over the bread and refrigerate overnight or until bread it totally soaked.
Sprinkle nuts and brown sugar over bread mixture.
Bake in a 12# Dutch Oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with syrup, a breakfast meat and coffee.
Yield 10-12 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour hot milk over bread in large bowl.
Blend eggs, sugar and vanilla together; add to bread and mix well.
Add raisins.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven until firm and golden brown.
Makes 24 servings.

title: betty salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.

title: no-bake pineapple cheese cake
directions: Prepare Jell-O first so it can cool.
Pour melted margarine into crumbs and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Set aside.
Whip Milnot and 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff.
Cream together cream cheese and cup of sugar.
Mix in Jell-O.
Add to Milnot and then stir in pineapple.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of filling and sprinkle additional graham cracker crumbs over top. Chill.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter over low heat; blend in flour and onion powder.
Slowly stir in the heated milk.
Stir with a wire wisk or wooden spoon over low heat until thickened and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in the cheese until melted; add hominy.
Pour into greased casserole dish; top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix jello, water; let jell slightly and add pineapple, bananas. Let jell. Blend juice, sugar, egg, flour, and butter. Cook until thick and add one 3 oz. pkg. cream cheese. Stir until melted and smooth. Let cool, then pour on top of jello. Very good! Makes large dish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Place vegetables in casserole dish.
Cut up chunks of Velveeta cheese and place on top of vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in microwave until cheese is melted.
Stir together. Melt butter in skillet.
Add crushed Ritz crackers and mix well. Spoon cracker mixture over top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: chicken pepper pasta
directions: Melt Country Morning Blend in a skillet.
Stir in onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat until slightly tender (2 or 3 minutes).
Remove from skillet, leaving juices in pan.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is brown and tender (7 to 9 minutes). Add vegetables, half and half, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese to chicken mixture.
Reduce heat and continue cooking until cheese melts (3 to 5 minutes).
Add cooked vermicelli to mixture.
Toss gently to coat.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sand cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and 10x sugar.
Set aside.

title: sweet relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with turmeric.
Dissolve salt in 2 quarts cold water.
Pour over vegetables and let stand for 3 to 4 hours.
Drain; cover vegetables with cold water and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Tie the spices in a bag; add to the brown sugar and vinegar.
Heat to boiling and pour over the vegetables.
Cover and let stand for 12 to 18 hours in a cool place.
Simmer until vegetables are hot. Bring to a boil; pour into jars and seal.

title: fresh peach muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle peaches with lemon juice and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, adding flour last.
Fold in fruit.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: prize cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugars; add eggs and beat until smooth. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to batter and blend well.
Add oatmeal and vanilla; blend well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: crisp zucchini pancakes
directions: Place shredded zucchini in colander.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside for 30 minutes.
Squeeze as much liquid out of zucchini as possible.
Saute onion in hot butter until tender.
Put zucchini and onion in large bowl.
Add eggs, flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and wheat germ.
Pour oil into skillet and heat.
Drop slightly rounded tablespoonfuls of zucchini mixture into oil; flatten to 3-inch diameter with back of spoon. Cook 1 minute on each side, or until golden.
Remove with slotted spoon; drain on paper towel.
Keep hot until all pancakes are ready.
Can melt cheese over top of each one.

title: dinner rolls or loaves
directions: Beat together all ingredients except flour.
Sit in a warm place, about 15 minutes or until real "bubbly."
Add flour to mixture and work until smooth.
Sit in a warm place until it doubles in bulk.
Punch down.
Shape into rolls.
Makes 48 rolls or can make 4 loaves bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: horseradish cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mayonnaise and horseradish.
Pour into small crock or bowl. Chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: homemade hot fudge sundae sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla.
Cook in saucepan until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool in water bath in sink, stirring 2 to 3 times while cooling down.
Serve over ice cream.
We like to think Sunday is a great day for a "Sundae".

title: chicken divan(microwave)
directions: Remove outer wrapping from broccoli packages and microwave at High for 3 minutes or until each package is flexible.
Arrange broccoli in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
In medium bowl, mix soup, sour cream, lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic powder.
Stir in chicken; pour over broccoli.
Set aside.
Melt butter in small bowl in microwave.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave at High for 12 to 14 minutes or until hot.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with water using pineapple juice for part of water. Add pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti.
Drain.
Fill with
meat mixture and place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with remaining meat.
Pour spaghetti sauce over all and top with cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies("the best")
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand for 1 hour, covered with plastic wrap.
Cream together the butter and sugars. Add four, salt, cinnamon and soda to sugar mixture.

Mix well. Blend in egg-raisin mixture, oatmeal and chopped nuts. Dough will be stiff. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet or roll into small balls and flatten slightly. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pork chops with herb dumplings
directions: Cook pork chops until brown on both sides.
Mix soup, mushrooms, water and sage.
Layer onion on chops.
Pour soup mixture over top.
Heat until boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: nana's "little bear" soup
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and bring to a boil.
Mix 1/2 cup milk and 2 tablespoons flour together.
Gradually stir into soup mixture.
Continue to cook stirring constantly until soup mixture thickens.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet on low to medium heat.
Saute onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Add Tabasco and Tony's (to taste).
Add crawfish and cook down 4 to 5 minutes.
Add Cream of Chicken soup.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add Jell-O mix and cool.
Add cottage cheese and stir.
Stir in Cool Whip and nuts; then refrigerate.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Spray Pam in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
In a small bowl, mash the canned shrimp and mix with softened cream cheese.
Add dill and blend.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften.
Beat egg yolk and sugar together in top of double boiler.
Stir in gelatin and cook the mixture over boiling water, stirring constantly until thick and fluffy.
(Takes about 4 minutes.)
Remove saucepan from
heat and stir in peanut butter.
I find that if you keep the mixture over hot (not boiling) water, the peanut butter will blend into the egg yolk, sugar and gelatin mixture better.
Let cool a little before adding egg white and cream.
Beat egg white until it stands in peaks.
In separate bowl, beat cream until it holds its shape. (If you use sour cream, no beating is necessary.)
Gently fold beaten egg white and whipped cream into gelatin mixture.
Pour into cool pie shell and refrigerate until firm.
May be garnished with dollops of whipped cream and crushed peanut brittle, if desired.

title: auntie mickey's italian stuffed peppers
directions: My grandmother made the best stuffed peppers.
She could not read or write, so it was difficult to get a recipe from her.
She would sometimes add raisins or "God's Fingers" (pine nuts) to her peppers.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Stir in beans, brown sugar, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and prepared mustard.
Turn into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir and top with bacon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat broccoli, butter and Cheez Whiz until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
After boiling, pour into a greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jiffy dinner stew
directions: Saute onion with hamburger; drain.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, beans and sugar.
Cook until beans are tender (20 minutes).
Mix water and flour; stir into stew.
Cook, stirring 1 minute.
Serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine; stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla. Gradually pour over popcorn.
Pour into 2 cookie sheets and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Turn corn every 15 minutes while baking.

title: aunt thursa's breast of chicken in white wine
directions: Wash and dry chicken; brown in butter in 6-quart Dutch oven. Remove chicken.
Add mushrooms, onion and garlic; saute 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add flour and seasonings; slowly add broth and cubes.
Bring to boil.
Stir.
Reduce heat and add wine.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Add chicken to sauce and bake covered for 30 minutes.
You may divide into 3 portions and freeze or continue baking about 40 minutes more.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, egg, bread crumbs, onion and black pepper. Roll out meatballs.
Put in microwave or oven until brown.

title: peach custard cake
directions: Mix butter with flour and salt with a pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse meal.
With back of a spoon, press mixture firmly on bottom and halfway up sides of a greased 8-inch square pan.

title: icebox pudding supreme
directions: Cut cake into slices about 1/2-inch thick and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Spoon one half of pudding over cake.
Cover with another layer of cake, then the rest of the pudding.
Refrigerate for about 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chocolate jimmies on top.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 11 x 14 x 2-inch pan.
Let cool; divide into thirds.
Mix pudding according to directions; let set. In a clear punch bowl, crumble 1/3 of cake.
Spread 1/3 pudding over it, then 1/3 of pineapple on this.
Add 1/3 of strawberry filling and nuts over pineapple.
Repeat twice.
Cover completely with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts and fresh strawberries.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Great with vegetables.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and freeze overnight. Mix in 2 bottles ginger ale when serving.

title: polish cabbage rolls("gobabki")
directions: Parboil cabbage until leaves may be separated (about 30 minutes); cool enough to handle.
Separate leaves and cut off thick membrane.

title: cherry cool whip salad
directions: Mix together well and chill for several hours.
(Blueberry pie filling is good also.)

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in a 2-quart baking dish and cook, covered, for 2 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: rice primavera
directions: In large skillet, cook mushrooms, onions, celery, pepper, bouillon and seasoning in oleo.
Add rice, cheese and carrots. Cook 5 minutes; toss lightly.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bo biscuits
directions: Mix together
flour,
sugar, baking powder and shortening. Mix until dough resembles corn meal.
Add buttermilk and stir together.
Knead
mintues.
Roll
dough
to
inch thick. Cut with large biscuit cutter.
Dip biscuits in melted margarine. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Heat milk.
Before it boils, add rice and 1/2 the sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Keep on medium to medium-high heat and cook 25 to 30 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Bake and cool pastry.
Fill pastry shell with ice cream. Spread evenly.
Wrap in foil; fold edges under to seal.
Freeze. Just before serving, top with fresh, frozen or canned fruit and whipped cream.

title: janey's election day cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Chop or cut dried beef and green onions.
Mix all ingredients and put in refrigerator until firm. Roll in large ball or balls, roll in nuts and serve with crackers.

title: diabetic rice cereal crust
directions: Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Chill well before filling.

title: hot cran apricot drink
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat 10 to 15 minutes until hot.
Serve hot in mugs or cups. Garnish with orange slice.
Yield:
6 cups.
Serving:
1 cup. Calories:
Fat:
0 grams.

title: old-fashioned egg custard
directions: Bring milk and butter to boil.
Beat eggs and sugar together. Fold eggs and sugar into milk, then add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes (the temperature is important).

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix coconut, flour, sugar and margarine in a large bowl, reserving about 1/2 of the coconut for later use.
Put the mixture in an 8 x 12-inch dish or pan.
Bake it 45 minutes or until brown, at 300°.
Remove from stove and cool.
Mix pudding by directions on box.

title: pizza bagels
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place spoonful sauce on 1/2 bagel and put on pepperoni slices.
Place about 2 tablespoons shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: meal in one
directions: Place potato slices in layers in bottom of ungreased casserole dish.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Place on top of potatoes.
Arrange ground meat on top of onion slices.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour tomatoes and juice on top of meat layer.
Break up tomatoes.
Insert knife around edge of casserole to allow juice to run down inside.
Bake 1 hour in 425° oven.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Coat meat with combined flour and seasonings.
Brown in oil; drain.
Combine meat, tomatoes, peas, mushrooms and onions; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover; bake at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until meat and onions are tender.
Combine potatoes and process cheese spread; spoon around edge of casserole.
Broil until process cheese spread begins to melt. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain off fat.
In a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish, layer potatoes and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Put sausage and onion over potatoes.
Beat eggs, milk and dry mustard and pour over dish.
Place cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour pork chops
directions: Brown chops; pour off excess fat.
Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add remaining ingredients to syrup; pour over chops in skillet.
Cook, covered, over low heat 1/2 hour or until tender, turning chops once or twice.
Remove meat to platter.
Stir fruit into sauce; heat to boiling.
Spoon some sauce over chops; pass remainder.
Makes six servings.

title: avocado and black bean, mango salad
directions: Place the beans, onion, tomatoes, pepper, corn, avocado and mango in a large bowl; toss lightly. Then add lettuce leaves and mix in salad dressing. Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add milk, then the butter. Beat egg
yolks	and
add to mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour
into	baked
pie
shell and top with meringue. Bake until top is light brown.

title: baked french toast
directions: Line bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan with half of the bread cubes. Layer cream cheese cubes on top of bread.
Arrange remaining bread cubes on top.
Beat together eggs, maple syrup and milk in a large bowl.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: jeweled fruitcake miniatures
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place baking cups in a muffin pan.
Spoon batter into
each cup.	Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or line 6 miniature loaf
pans,
x 5/8 x 1 1/2 inches with aluminum
foil; grease.
Divide batter among pans; spread evenly. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix shortening, eggs, and sugar together.
Slowly add dry ingredients.
Mix well then add chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: easy stew
directions: Layer onion in bottom of Dutch oven or crock-pot; then layer stew meat, potatoes and carrots.
Pour soups on meat and vegetables.
Do not mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours or low in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.
Stir to mix gravy and serve. You may add any vegetable you choose.

title: french fry casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add soups; mix well.
Add vegetables; mix well. Top with French fries.
(You can mix them in, also.) Bake at 350° until fries are done.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Combine
flour, sugar, baking powder and salt
in
a
large bowl.
Whisk oil, milk, eggs and almond extract in another bowl until smooth.
Add dry ingredients; mix only
until
evenly moistened.
Stir in poppy seed. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt the chocolate and oleo.
Stir in the sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a rolling boil; remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Very good on vanilla ice cream or plain cake.

title: stewed chestnut chicken
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Add ginger, green onion and chicken; stir-fry until chicken changes color.
Add salt, sugar and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup of water; simmer for another 30 minutes. Add chestnuts; simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together and salt and pepper to taste.

title: nutty noodles
directions: Melt chips and pour in noodles and peanuts.
Stir until covered well.
Spoon out on wax paper by teaspoon.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Mix well and form into small balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Allow to cool on cookie sheet.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in 11 x 7-inch baking dish (I use 9 x 13-inch).
Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry; mix well.
Slice chicken and arrange on broccoli.
Pour sauce over this and top with cheese, bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and salt to taste.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.
Transfer to 10-inch square baking dish.
Make corn bread batter and pour over top of meat mixture.
Bake uncovered in a 425° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: black beans and rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine broth, coconut and margarine. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir in beans and onions.
Cover and cook an additional 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 6 (2/3 cup) servings.

title: coconut easter eggs
directions: Cream together butter, salt and milk.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and coconut.
Shape into egg and place in freezer until very cold and ready to dip.
Put into double boiler, the chocolate and wax.
Dip eggs.
Keep stirring chocolate.
Keep pan over hot water, but remove from gas.
Store eggs in refrigerator or freezer.

title: dumplings
directions: Place the dry ingredients into a mixing bowl. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix the batter, but do not let it be too thick or too loose.
In a large pot, boil water. Turn the heat down to medium. Drop by tablespoon into the boiling water. Do not crowd the pot.
Cook the dumplings in the water until you can put a fork into them and they are not soggy (about 10 minutes). Cover for another 3 to 5 minutes, continuing to cook them on medium heat.

title: the salad
directions: Cook the carrots in small amount of boiling salted water until crisp-tender.
Drain and chill.
Cook the peas according to package instructions.
Drain and chill.
Place the lettuce
in large glass or other salad bowl and season with salt and pepper. Arrange the carrots, celery, peas, onion, sliced olives and bacon in layers over lettuce.
Spread 1 cup Blender Mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with sugar.
Garnish with whole olives and parsley and serve with remaining Blender Mayonnaise.
Commercial mayonnaise may be substituted for Blender Mayonnaise.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: butter rolls
directions: Take a piece of aluminum foil and pour some flour onto it. Flatten each biscuit with rolling pin.
Place 2 pats of butter and a tablespoon of sugar in the middle of the rolled out biscuit. Fold over and pinch edges together.
Place this in baking dish. Continue until all biscuits are used.
After filling up the pan, place butter pats on each top and sprinkle with sugar.
Pour enough milk around sides that the tops are just above the milk. Place in 450° oven and bake until golden brown.
Deelish!!!

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a nonstick baking sheet with the vegetable oil.
Scrub the potatoes thoroughly under running water; pat dry.
Slice them lengthwise into 1/4-inch thick slices, then cut into fries of the desired size.
Pat the fries dry.
In a medium bowl, beat the egg whites with a whisk until foamy.
Add the potatoes and toss until coated.
Arrange the fries in a single layer on the baking sheet.
Bake until crisp and lightly brown and tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Makes 2 servings.

title: roast turkey
directions: Rinse bird well on the outside as well as inside the body and neck cavities.
Be sure to remove giblets from both cavities. Reserve for making giblet gravy.
Rub salt (and pepper, if desired) in cavities and on outside of bird.
Place onion and celery in body cavity.
Pull neck skin to the back and fasten with a small skewer. Tuck drumsticks under band of skin at the tail or tie them securely to the tail; thread can be used.
Place bird, breast side up, in covered roasting pan.
Brush skin with melted oleo.
Add 2 cups water to roaster.
Cover bird with water-drenched cheesecloth or doubled paper towels.
Cover roaster and bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 4 to 4 1/2 hours.
Every hour, remoisten toweling with broth from roaster.
Remove roaster cover, cut skin band or thread on drumsticks.
Cook, uncovered, during the last 30 minutes to allow for light golden browning of bird.
When done, drumsticks should feel very soft when pressed.

title: sauerkraut meatballs
directions: Mix chili sauce, water, sauerkraut, sugar and cranberry sauce in pan; heat to blend.
Mix remaining ingredients; form into small, walnut size meatballs.
Place meatballs in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes. Serve with toothpicks or spoon for appetizer or main dish.
The men love it especially.

title: easy pie
directions: Fold together the condensed milk, lemon juice, pineapple and Cool Whip. Pour into pie crusts. Set in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.

title: low sodium super rice(diabetic)
directions: Dissolve 2 chicken bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water. Add rice; bring to a boil again.
Cover; let simmer for 14 minutes.
Cook peas, adding sweetener at the last minute.
In a skillet, saute onion and mushrooms in oil.
Add peas, onion and mushrooms to rice.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 8 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt
butter in pan,
pour
in
fruit
with
juice.
Mix flour, sugar and milk
together and pour over butter and fruit. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Scald milk; beat eggs well.
Mix all ingredients; beat well. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.

title: peanut butter marshmallow fudge
directions: Measure all ingredients before you commence.
Cook sugar and milk to soft ball.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered dish.
(Be sure dish is buttered before you start cooking.)
Yield: 2 pounds.

title: caesar salad
directions: Pour vinegar over anchovies in bowl; cut anchovies up with knife and fork, then mince with 2 forks.
Let stand.
Add salt and pepper to torn lettuce in bowl; toss.
Let stand.
Squeeze juice of lemon into another bowl; add coddled egg, Worcestershire sauce and minced garlic.
Add minced anchovies and vinegar.
Mix well before adding to lettuce.
Toss well, then add olive oil and cheese; toss again.
Add croutons; toss again and serve.
Serves 2 as a dinner.

title: dried chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Cut
beef into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients with beef
and
add to cream cheese.
Makes 1 large or 2 small balls. (Save some of the pieces of beef to lay on top, if you wish.)

title: leftover turkey
directions: Place broccoli in baking dish.
Layer with bite-size turkey. Mix milk with soup.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: good and easy dessert
directions: Bake cake mix as directed, using a sheet cake pan, 2 x 10 1/2 x 15-inch.
Drain the pineapple well.
While cake is cooling, beat the cream cheese until smooth.
Add pudding mix and milk slowly to make a smooth pudding.

title: cheese pit
directions: Butter casserole.
Alternate bread and cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cheese cake
directions: Follow directions for instant cheesecake, adding the peanut butter to filling mix. Chill and cut into small squares. Very rich, but heavenly taste.

title: bermuda summer salad
directions: Fry bacon and slice mushrooms; set aside.
Tear lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Slice onion and separate into rings. Layer lettuce and onion rings on a platter.

Combine sour cream, 3 teaspoons of sugar and enough milk to thin mixture. Drizzle over the lettuce and onions. Combine the mayonnaise, remaining sugar and enough milk to thin the mixture to drizzle over the sour cream mixture on the lettuce and onions. Sprinkle on the sliced mushrooms, crumbled bacon and Parmesan cheese. Do not pre-mix the 2 glazes and do not toss the salad. Chill for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: quincy's potato soup
directions: Saute butter, onions and parsley until onions are tender.
Add water to the potatoes and salt.
Cook until almost done.
Add soup, milk and sour cream, stirring occasionally, until it comes to a boil.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease, then add all of the ingredients.

title: crescent surprises
directions: Break peanut butter cups in half.
Wrap 2 pieces in crescent roll and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: sunflower fettuccine
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water according to package directions; drain.
Return noodles to saucepan.
Stir in light cream and margarine until margarine melts.
Toss in sunflower kernels, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well. Bake at 350° until brown (1 hour).

title: linguine a la marinara (sauce)
directions: Pour olive oil in pan and add all ingredients except macaroni. Simmer for 45 minutes.
Boil macaroni; drain.
Pour sauce on top. Finish off with Parmesan or Locatelli cheese.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Melt butter and pour over casserole.
Crush crackers and cover casserole. Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine vegetables; mix remaining ingredients and pour over salad.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: reese's peanut butter cup
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, peanut butter, sugar and butter.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Pour over mixture.
Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Cut and refrigerate again.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Grease large pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch) well; sprinkle all marshmallows in pan.
Prepare strawberries by combining with the strawberry Jell-O; let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; blend well.
Pour batter over marshmallows. Spoon strawberry mixture over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
